{{skill infobox | name = "Save Yourselves!" | campaign = Factions | profession = Warrior | attribute = Allegiance rank | pve-only = y | type = Shout | adrenaline = 8 | causes1 = Increased Armor Rating | description = [[Shout]]. For {{gr2|4|6}} seconds, all other [[party member]]s gain +100 [[Armor rating|armor]]. | concise description = Shout. ({{gr2|4|6}} seconds.) All other party members gain +100 armor. | aoe = earshot | id = 1954<!-- Luxon -->, 2097<!-- Kurzick --> }}
{{ Skill progression max12 | title track = [[Allegiance rank]] | var1 name = [[Duration]] | var1 at0 = 4 | var1 at12 = 6 }}
== Acquisition == * [[Kurzick Bureaucrat]] ([[House zu Heltzer]] and [[Kurzick]]-allied [[guild hall]]s) * [[Luxon Scavenger]] ([[Cavalon]] and [[Luxon]]-allied guild halls)
== Notes == * Good [[adrenaline]] management is essential to quickly refill the adrenaline pool of this skill to make up for its short duration. ** [["For Great Justice!"]] works well in that regard, as it is also a warrior skill and does not require any investment. * After reaching the first [[allegiance rank]], Kurzick/Luxon Supporter, [[level]] 20 [[character]]s may learn this skill from a Kurzick Bureaucrat or Luxon Scavenger for 3,000 faction. * The [[skill icon]] for the Kurzick version is on top, and the icon for the Luxon version is on the bottom. * +100 armor reduces non-[[armor-ignoring damage]] by 82.3%. * An [[Imbagon]] is a paragon build that maintains both "Save Yourselves!" and [["There's Nothing to Fear!"]] for up to 88.5% total damage reduction on other party members. {{Anomaly|The skill descriptions omit that only party members within [[earshot]] are affected.}}
==Trivia== * Unlike other [[allegiance skill]]s, the maximum effectiveness of "Save Yourselves!" is reached at rank 5 instead of 6. * This skill has changed since its introduction; see its [[/Skill history|skill history]] for details.

