__NOTOC__{{Skill infobox | id = 2112 | name = "There's Nothing to Fear!" | campaign = Nightfall | profession = Paragon | attribute = Sunspear rank | pve-only = y | type = Shout | energy = 15 | recharge = 20 | causes1 = Damage Reduction | causes2 = Healing | description = [[Shout]]. For 4 seconds and 1 second for every 2 ranks in [[Leadership]], all [[party]] members [[within earshot]] take {{gr2|20|35}}% less [[damage]]. Affected party members are [[heal]]ed for {{gr2|35|60}} [[Health]] when this shout ends. | concise description = Shout. (4 seconds plus 1 second for every 2 ranks in Leadership.) Reduces damage by {{gr2|20|35}}% for party members in earshot. End effect: heals for {{gr2|35|60}} Health. }}
{{Skill progression max10 | title track = [[Sunspear rank]] | var1 name = % [[Damage reduction]] | var1 at0 = 20 | var1 at10 = 35 | var2 name = [[Heal]]ing | var2 at0 = 35 | var2 at10 = 60 }}
{{Skill progression | attribute = [[Leadership]] | maximum = 18 | var1 name = [[Duration]] | var1 at0 = 4 | var1 at15 = 11.25}}
==Acquisition== '''[[Hero skill trainer]]s''' *[[Pikin]] ([[Kamadan, Jewel of Istan]]) *[[Shiloh]] ([[Sunspear Great Hall]]) *[[Libeh]] ([[Command Post]])
==Related skills== * {{skill icon|"They're on Fire!"}} * {{skill icon|"There's Nothing to Fear!" (Thackeray)}}
==Notes== *If you recast this skill while it is still active, the healing effect will not happen. *To determine the total damage reduction when combining skills like [["They're on Fire!"]], multiply the % of damage not reduced of each skill by each other, and the result is the % of damage your affected party takes (provided all conditions are met). **Example (assuming all conditions are met, i.e. burning, in earshot, etc.): ***"They're on Fire!" at [[Leadership]] 12 = 29% reduction / 71% damage ***"There's Nothing to Fear!" at Sunspear rank 5 to 10 = 35% reduction / 65% damage ***(ToF) .71 x (TNtF) .65 = .46 (or 46% damage is received / 54% reduction) {{bug|When sorting skills by campaign, this is listed under [[Core]] although it's a Nightfall skill.}}
==Trivia== *This skill name was inspired by the [[w:Franklin_D._Roosevelt|Franklin D. Roosevelt]] speech referencing the phrase "...the only thing we have to fear is fear itself..." ([http://wiki.guildwars.com/index.php?title=User_talk:Emily_Diehl/Trivia_archive&oldid=204605#.22There.27s_Nothing_to_Fear.21.22 source]).
{{DEFAULTSORT:There's Nothing to Fear!}} [[Category:Paragon PvE-only skills]] [[Category:Skills offered by hero skill trainers]]

