__NOTOC__{{Skill infobox | id = 1115 | name = Air of Enchantment | campaign = Factions | profession = Monk | attribute = Protection Prayers | type = Enchantment Spell | elite = y | energy = 5 | activation = {{1/4}} | recharge = 8 | target = other allies | range = | aoe = none | causes1 = Decreased Energy Cost | causes2 = | removes1 = | requires1 = | description = [[Elite]] [[Enchantment Spell]]. For {{gr|4|10}} seconds, enchantments cast on [[target]] other [[ally]] cost 5 less [[Energy]] (minimum 1 Energy). | concise description = Elite Enchantment Spell. ({{gr|4|10}} seconds.) Enchantments cast on target ally cost 5 less Energy (minimum 1 Energy). {{gray|Cannot self-target.}} }}
{{Skill progression |attribute = [[Protection Prayers]] |var1 name = [[Duration]] |var1 at0 = 4 |var1 at15 = 10}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Signet of Capture]]''' * [[Jayne Forestlight]] ([[The Eternal Grove (explorable area)]]) * [[Miella Lightwing]] ([[Silent Surf]])
== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Divine Spirit}} * {{skill icon|Healer's Covenant}} ([[elite]]) * {{skill icon|Selfless Spirit}}
== Notes == * Air of Enchantment reduces the energy cost of all enchantments, both targeted and self-targeting. ** This includes self-targeting enchantments such as [[Flash Enchantments]] and [[Attunements]]. ** Party wide enchantments that do not target an ally (such as [[Aegis]] and [[Orders]] enchantments) will have their energy cost reduced if used by the recipient of Air of Enchantment. ** [[Doublecast]] Enchantment Spells are affected only if the target is under Air of Enchantment, not if the caster is (despite the caster also becoming enchanted when the skill finishes activation).
== Trivia == * The functionality of this skill has changed since its introduction; see its [[{{PAGENAME}}/Skill history|skill revision history]] for details.
