__NOTOC__{{Skill infobox | id = 832 | name = Animate Flesh Golem | campaign = Factions | profession = Necromancer | attribute = Death Magic | type = Spell | elite = y | energy = 10 | activation = 3 | recharge = 30 | target = corpse | range = Casting | aoe = none | causes1 = Exploits Corpse | causes2 = Minion | requires1 = Corpse | description = [[Elite]] [[Spell]]. Exploit nearest [[corpse]] to animate a [[level]] {{gr|3|25}} [[Flesh Golem]]. The Flesh Golem leaves an exploitable corpse. You can have only one Flesh Golem at a time. | concise description = Elite Spell. Creates a level {{gr|3|25}} flesh golem which leaves a fresh corpse when it dies. {{gray|Exploits a fresh corpse. You can have only one flesh golem at a time.}} }}
{{Skill progression |attribute = [[Death Magic]] |var1 name = [[Level]] |var1 at0 = 3 |var1 at15 = 25}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Signet of Capture]]''' * [[Ghial the Bone Dancer]] ([[Xaquang Skyway]])
== Notes == * An exploitable corpse has a few notable consequences : ** [[Taste of Death]] or [[Feast for the Dead]] can be used more effectively, for instance to respectively make [[Blood of the Master]] safer or keep the minion army alive longer. ** Recycling the Flesh Golem summoning allows to always have one alive. * A Flesh Golem's size is determined by its level; the higher the level, the larger the minion.
