__NOTOC__{{Skill infobox | name = Animate Shambling Horror | id = 1351 | campaign = Nightfall | profession = Necromancer | attribute = Death Magic | type = Spell | energy = 15 | activation = 3 | recharge = 25 | target = untargeted | range = Casting | aoe = none | causes1 = Exploits Corpse | causes2 = Minion | causes3 = Bleeding | requires1 = Corpse | description = [[Spell]]. Exploit nearest [[corpse]] to create a [[level]] {{gr|1|17}} [[Shambling Horror|shambling horror]]. When the shambling horror [[Death|dies]], it is replaced by a level {{gr|0|15}} [[jagged horror]] that causes [[Bleeding]] with each of its [[attack]]s. | concise description = Spell. Creates a level {{gr|1|17}} shambling horror. When the shambling horror dies, it is replaced by a level {{gr|0|15}} jagged horror that causes Bleeding with each of its attacks. {{gray|Exploits a fresh corpse.}} }}
{{Skill progression |attribute = [[Death Magic]] |var1 name = [[Shambling Horror]] [[level]] |var1 at0 = 1 |var1 at15 = 17 |var2 name = [[Jagged Horror]] level |var2 at0 = 0 |var2 at15 = 15 }}
== Acquisition == '''[[Skill trainer]]''' * [[Tohn]] ([[Kamadan, Jewel of Istan]]) '''[[Hero skill trainer]]''' * [[Shiloh]] ([[Sunspear Great Hall]])
== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Jagged Bones}} ([[elite]])
== Notes == * When the Shambling Horror dies, the [[spawn]]ed Jagged Horror will trigger [[Explosive Growth]], [[Boon of Creation]], and [[Spirit's Gift]]. * Shambling Horrors are good targets for [[Taste of Death]] and [[Feast for the Dead]], since it leaves a Jagged Horror when it dies. * When combined with [[Jagged Bones]], two Jagged Horrors are produced. * The level of the Jagged Horror is determined by the Death Magic rank of the caster when the Shambling Horror was created. * [[Masterless minion|Masterless]] Shambling Horrors do not spawn a Jagged Horror when they die. * This skill has a much longer recharge when compared to most animation skills, and thus cannot be relied upon alone to create a full army of minions. * The bleeding lasts for 25 seconds. {{anomaly|The descriptions do not mention the [[duration]] of the bleeding inflicted by the Jagged Horror.}}
