{{Skill infobox | id = 1062 | name = Arcane Larceny | campaign = Factions | profession = Mesmer | attribute = Domination Magic | type = Spell | energy = 10 | activation = 1 | special = duplicate | causes1 = Disable | causes2 = Skill Copying | description = [[Spell]]. For {{gr|5|35}} seconds, one random spell is [[disable]]d for [[target]] [[foe]] and Arcane Larceny is replaced by that spell. | concise description = Spell. ({{gr|5|35}} seconds.) Disables one random spell. This skill becomes that spell. | target = foes }}
{{Skill progression |attribute = [[Domination Magic]] |var1 name = [[Duration]] |var1 at0 = 5 |var1 at15 = 35}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Skill trainer]]s''' * [[Michiko]] ([[Kaineng Center]]) * [[Akane]] ([[Senji's Corner]]) * [[Zytka]] ([[House zu Heltzer]])
== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Arcane Thievery}} ([[duplicate skill]]) * {{skill icon|Simple Thievery}} ([[elite]]) * {{skill icon|Smooth Criminal}}
== Notes == * This cannot be activated on a target with no spells. ''"That target has no spells to steal."'' appears when you attempt to. * If you die when the duration of Arcane Larceny has not ended, the stolen spell on your [[skill bar]] will revert back to Arcane Larceny (similar to [[Skill quick reference#Skills that are replaced with other skills|other skills that can copy skills]]); however, the target's spell will remain disabled for the full duration. This allows you to use Arcane Larceny to disable two spells at the same time if you are [[Resurrection|resurrected]] before the disable duration of the prior use of Arcane Larceny has ended. * This can be used to interfere with [[skill chain]]s on [[profession]]s that tend to use only a few spells, e.g. primary [[Assassin]]s.
[[de:Arkane Entwendung]]

{{redirect 2|"AM"|the mission|[[Abaddon's Mouth]]}} {{Skill infobox | id = 65 | name = Arcane Mimicry | campaign = Core | profession = Mesmer | type = Spell | energy = 15 | recharge = 60 | activation = 2 | causes1 = Skill Copying | description = [[Spell]]. For 20 seconds, Arcane Mimicry becomes the non-[[form]] [[elite skill]] from [[target]] other [[ally]]. | concise description = Spell. This skill becomes target ally's elite skill (20 seconds). {{gray|Cannot self-target. No effect if target's elite skill is a form.}} | target = other allies }}
== Acquisition == '''[[Skill trainer]]s''' * [[Prophecies]] ** [[Avena]] ([[Maguuma Stade]]) ** [[Tengsao]] ([[The Amnoon Oasis]]) ** [[Dakk]] ([[Ember Light Camp]]) * [[Factions]] ** [[Michiko]] ([[Kaineng Center]]) ** [[Zytka]] ([[House zu Heltzer]]) ** [[Akane]] ([[Senji's Corner]]) * [[Nightfall]] ** [[Medando]] ([[Yohlon Haven]]) ** [[Yuli]] ([[Grand Court of Sebelkeh]]) '''[[Hero skill trainer]]s''' * Nightfall ** [[Warden of Whispers (Chantry of Secrets)|Warden of Whispers]] ([[Chantry of Secrets]])
== Notes == * When using Arcane Mimicry on an ally that has more than one elite skill, the first elite skill from the left on their [[skill bar]] is copied. Accordingly, keep Arcane Mimicry to the right of any intended elite skill(s) if the team [[build]] requires mutual mimicry. * If used on an ally without a non-form elite skill, Arcane Mimicry [[recharge]]s instead. **Heroes (and presumably other NPCs) cannot use this skill to copy ''any'' [[List_of_Anniversary_Celebration_elite_skills|PvE-only skill]]. * A successful Arcane Mimicry does not recharge like other skills: after the copy effect ends, the skill is [[disable]]d for 60 seconds. * [[Upkeep|Maintained enchantments]], [[Upkeep#Skills that last indefinitely without an upkeep|skills that last indefinitely without an upkeep]] or [[Renewal effect|skills that renew themselves]] copied with Arcane Mimicry will continue to be maintained, active or renewable even after expiration of Arcane Mimicry copy effect. * [[Signet of Illusions]] or [[Symbols of Inspiration]] can be used to boost the attribute rank of a relevant copied elite. * Players are able to copy elite skills which are not available from their skill list, but use them only when certain conditions are met: ** if the skill is a core skill or belongs to a campaign available on the [[account]], the player (and their [[hero]]es) can use it even if it has not been [[unlock]]ed. ** if the skill belongs to a campaign unavailable to the account, it will be copied to the skill bar but cannot be used by the playable character (remaining [[Skill icon#Locked skills|locked]] like PvE-only skills are in a PvP area). ** heroes are able to copy and use skills from any campaigns available and unavailable to an account, but the player cannot force the use of skills from campaigns unavailable to them. * Heroes prioritize which elite they copy as follows: *# Elites from the hero's primary [[profession]]. *# High rank in the relevant attribute. *# [[No Attribute Skill]]s. ** The [[AI]] will never choose to copy an elite unless they have at least rank six in the required attribute (including any modifications). ''No Attribute'' Skills can always be copied. * Heroes will use the copied skill as they normally would do. ** Maintained enchantments that heroes would dismiss can be disabled to be maintained for the duration of the copy effect. When the copy effect ends the enchantment will be dropped as soon as the AI dictates it to (i.e. the hero is not in a situation where it would normally maintain the enchantment). {{anomaly|No effect if target's elite skill is [[Junundu Siege]].}} * Good synergy with [[Assassin's Promise]] and [[Air of Superiority]] to bypass the high recharge time. [[Category:Skills offered by hero skill trainers]]

