== Acquisition == '''[[Signet of Capture]]''' * [[Maligo Libens]] ([[Hell's Precipice]]) * [[Cerris]] ([[Nebo Terrace (War in Kryta)]])
== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Animate Bone Horror}} * {{skill icon|Masochism}}
== Notes == * Aura of the Lich does not target a corpse, and is unaffected by equipping a [[Bloodstained Insignia]]. * This skill is the only way to raise a [[minion]] without any corpses being available. * The +1 Death Magic buff activates after any minions are summoned. * The skill indeed exploits ''all'' corpses in range regardless of how many minions the caster's allowed to control, in this case the extra minions will die immediately. ** This will often replenish the caster's energy provided they have points in [[Soul Reaping]]. * The [[AI]] will let Aura of the Lich expire before recasting it, not utilizing it to the fullest.
== Trivia == * The figure in the [[skill icon]] is the [[Undead Lich]] and this skill is likely named after him, though he doesn't use it. * The [[functionality]] of this skill has changed since its introduction; see its [[Aura of the Lich/Skill history|skill history]] for details.
