== Acquisition == '''[[Skill trainer]]s''' * [[Ephaz]] ([[Beetletun]]) * [[Master Scout Kiera]] ([[Henge of Denravi]]) * [[Dakk]] ([[Ember Light Camp]]) '''[[Signet of Capture]]''' * [[Clobberhusk]] ([[Lornar's Pass]])
== Notes == * Both the full and concise descriptions fail to note that the [[target]] is also blinded. * [[Normal mode]] [[foe]] [[AI]] will use this skill on any target, including a target that is not knocked down; they will not wait to use this skill on a knocked down target even if they have a skill that can cause knock down (e.g. [[Grawl (Shiverpeaks)|Grawl]]). [[Hero]] and [[hard mode]] foe AI will only use this skill on a knocked down target.<!--Tested on the [[Doppelganger]] (with only Belly Smash and [[Hammer Bash]] equipped) and [[Grawl (Shiverpeaks)|Grawl]].-->
== Trivia == * One of the few skills that tries to explain its effect ("...the resulting dust cloud..."). In the past many skills were described in this way, but the introduction of [[Concise description|concise skill descriptions]] led to most of them being removed. Before Prophecies was released in 2005, the skill described blood spatter rather than a dust cloud. Similarly the target had to be "on the ground."

