__NOTOC__{{Skill infobox | id = 119 | name = Blood is Power | campaign = Core | profession = Necromancer | attribute = Blood Magic | type = Enchantment Spell | elite = yes | energy = 1 | activation = {{1/4}} | sacrifice = 33% | causes1 = Energy Regeneration | description = [[Elite]] [[Enchantment Spell]]. For 10 seconds, [[target]] other [[ally]] gains +{{gr|3|6}} [[Energy regeneration]]. | concise description = Elite Enchantment Spell. (10 seconds.) +{{gr|3|6}} Energy regeneration. {{gray|Cannot self-target.}} | target = other allies }}
{{Skill progression |attribute = [[Blood Magic]] |var1 name = [[Energy regeneration]] |var1 at0 = 3 |var1 at15 = 6}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Signet of Capture]]''' * [[Prophecies]] ** [[Cry Darkday]] ([[Snake Dance]]) * [[Factions]] ** [[Chan the Dragon's Blood]] ([[The Undercity]]) * [[Nightfall]] ** [[Overseer Haubeh]] ([[Kodonur Crossroads]]) ** [[Taskmaster Vanahk]] (Kodonur Crossroads) ** [[Lieutenant Vanahk]] ([[Yatendi Canyons]])
== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Blood Ritual}}
== Notes == {{see|Battery}} * The health sacrifice is rounded half to even and can be as low as 0 if the maximum health of the user is low enough, which makes it possible to continuously use the skill without actually losing health. ** To reach 1 health, a character can wear multiple armor pieces with superior attribute [[rune]]s, stack [[Death Penalty]] and even wear some [[equipment]] such as the -50 health [[Grim Cesta (knife)|Grim Cesta]] or [[offhand]] items with a [["Life is Pain"]] inscription. ** [[Awaken the Blood]] does not increase the health sacrifice to a lethal amount for a character with a maximum health of 1. * [[Hero]]es are often better than [[player]]s for impromptu use of this skill as they know how much [[energy]] each of their allies currently have, such as [[henchmen]]. ** Heroes will never use this skill on [[martial]] professions—unless they are wielding a [[wand]] or [[staff]]—and will reserve the use of this skill until a martial ally drops to less than half of their maximum energy. ** Heroes will always use this skill on [[spellcaster]] professions—regardless of what [[weapon]] they are wielding—and will reserve the use of this skill until a spellcaster ally drops to less than half of their maximum energy. {{Bug|Heroes will spam this skill on allies with heavy [[overcast]], regardless of what percentage of energy the ally has.}}
== Trivia == *This skill has changed since its introduction; see its [[/Skill history|skill revision history]] for details.
