{{Skill infobox | name = Call to the Torment | campaign = Nightfall | special = Monster | type = Skill | recharge = 20 | causes1= Summoned Creature | description = [[Skill (skill type)|Skill]]. [[Creature]] [[emote|kneels]] for 5 seconds and takes double [[damage]]. After 5 seconds, a duplicate of the creature is summoned to this location. | concise description = Skill. (5 seconds.) Creature kneels and takes double damage. End effect: a duplicate of the creature is summoned to this location. }}
==Notes== *Creatures summoned by this skill spawn with full health and energy, and can use this skill themselves. *Creatures summoned by this skill will not [[drop]] loot, give [[Lightbringer rank|Lightbringer promotion points]] or provide [[experience]] points. *This skill cannot be [[interrupt]]ed. Once it has been activated, the only way to prevent the duplicate from being summoned is by killing the creature who used this skill within the 5 seconds interval. *This skill is used by most [[Torment creature]]s in the [[Realm of Torment]] once their health drops below 50%. [[Boss]]es do not use this skill. *Creatures summoned by this skills are not considered part of any party and can be pulled separately from the party that summoned it. *Creatures summoned by this are able to be healed by Heart Tormentors, the Ruk in room 1 of Foundry, and also any margonite Ki or Ruk that is in the 5th room of Foundry, City, Part of Jadoth or any shadow enemies that wander in Gloom and Veil can also heal these mobs. [https://youtu.be/un_TsgxQ7cc A more indepth video on duplication. ] {{anomaly| Creatures summoned by this skill are not treated as [[summoned creature]]s by other skills, such as [[Banish]].}}
