{{Skill progression max10 |title track = [[Ebon Vanguard rank]] |var1 name = [[Armor-ignoring damage]] |var1 at0 = 18 |var1 at10 = 30 |var2 name = [[Bleeding]] [[duration]] |var2 at0 = 18 |var2 at10 = 30 }}
==Acquisition== '''[[Skill quest]]s''' *[[Mano a Norn-o]] ([[Eye of the North (outpost)|Eye of the North]])
==Related skills== *{{skill icon|Body Blow}} *{{skill icon|Chest Thumper}}
==Notes== *This skill also works with [[spellcasting weapon]]s, not just [[bow]]s and [[spear]]s. *This skill inflicts the longest bleeding duration amongst all player-useable skills in the game for attribute ranks below 19. *Amongst the ranged attacks with an activation time of {{1/2}} second or less, Deft Strike has a short recharge time. This can make the skill somewhat useful for skills that trigger on [[attack]]s or [[attack skill]]s, such as [[Nightmare Weapon]] or [[preparation]]s.
== Trivia == * Despite the [[skill icon]] showing the [[Ebon Vanguard]] making a deft strike with his [[sword]], this skill is ranged. * This generic ranged attack skill is the only one that can be used by player [[character]]s. It is also the only pure attack skill that can be used with a wand or staff. Previously, [[Smite]] was considered an attack skill and worked similarly, but was changed before the release of [[Guild Wars Nightfall|Nightfall]]. * In [[w:D&D|Dungeons & Dragons]], Deft Strike is the name of a Rogue attack. That attack, however, can be used with both melee and ranged weapons. [[Category:References to Dungeons & Dragons]]

