__NOTOC__ {{Skill infobox | id = 1091 | name = Double Dragon | campaign = Factions | profession = Elementalist | attribute = Fire Magic | type = Enchantment Spell | energy = 10 | activation = 1 | recharge = 20 | elite = y | aoe = adjacent | target = allies | causes1 = Burning | causes2 = Fire Damage | description = [[Elite]] [[Enchantment Spell]]. Invoke the power of the Dragon. For 8 seconds, you and [[target]] [[ally]] are enchanted with Double Dragon. [[Adjacent]] [[foe]]s are dealt {{gr|5|30}} [[fire damage]] each second. Additionally, when you or your ally use [[skill]]s that target a foe, that foe is set [[Burning|on fire]] for {{gr|0|3}} second[s]. | concise description = Elite Enchantment Spell. (8 seconds.) Enchants you and target ally. Adjacent foes take {{gr|5|30}} fire damage each second. Skills that target a foe also inflict Burning ({{gr|0|3}} second[s]). }}
{{Skill progression |attribute = [[Fire Magic]] |var1 name = [[Fire damage]] |var1 at0 = 5 |var1 at15 = 30 |var2 name = [[Burning]] [[duration]] |var2 at0 = 0 |var2 at15 = 3 }}
==Acquisition== '''[[Signet of Capture]]''' *[[Lian, Dragon's Petal]] ([[Wajjun Bazaar]]) *[[Lale the Vindictive]] ([[The Undercity]], during [[Chasing Zenmai]]) *[[Eri, Heart of Fire]] ([[Bukdek Byway]], during [[There Goes the Neighborhood]])
==Related skills== {{see|Doublecast skill}} *{{skill icon|Ancestors' Rage (PvP)}} *{{skill icon|Balthazar's Aura}} *{{skill icon|Elemental Flame}} *{{skill icon|Glyph of Immolation}} *{{skill icon|Storm of Swords}}
==Notes== *As with any [[doublecast skill]], [[NPC]]s will use this skill as soon as there is an enemy within the spell's [[area of effect]] range of an ally. *If a foe is targeted, the nearest ally (which can be the caster) will be enchanted instead. If nothing is targeted, Double Dragon will only be applied to the caster (the nearest ally). **This is the only offensive doublecast skill that does not deal double damage when targeting yourself, because Double Dragon does not have an [[initial effect]]. This is due to game mechanics: you cannot be affected by two of the same enchantment. {{anomaly|If a foe with a [[spell targeting prevention]] skill is targeted, Double Dragon will fail, despite the enchantment applying to the ''ally'' nearest to the target foe.}} {{anomaly|Whenever a target under the effects of Double Dragon is [[interrupt]]ed, the animation restarts.}} {{anomaly|Unlike most [[area damage over time]] skills, Double Dragon does not cause [[AI]] to [[scatter]].}}
==Trivia== *Double Dragon is the name of a [[w:Double Dragon (series)|series of video games]]. *The functionality of this skill has changed since its introduction; see its [[{{PAGENAME}}/Skill history|skill history]] for details.
