{{Skill infobox | id = 2233 | name = Ebon Battle Standard of Honor | campaign = Eye of the North | attribute = Ebon Vanguard rank | type = Ward Spell | energy = 10 | recharge = 20 | activation = 1 | pve-only = y | description = [[Ward Spell]]. You plant an Ebon Battle Standard of Honor at your current location. For {{gr2|14|20}} seconds, non-[[spirit]] [[Ally|allies]] [[In the area|in this area]] strike for +{{gr2|8|15}} [[damage]] and an additional +{{gr2|7|10}} vs. [[Charr]]. | concise description = Ward Spell. ({{gr2|14|20}} seconds.) Allies in this ward deal +{{gr2|8|15}} damage and +{{gr2|7|10}} more damage against Charr. {{gray|Spirits are unaffected.}} }}
{{skill progression max10 | title track = [[Ebon Vanguard rank]] | var1 name = [[Duration]] | var1 at0 = 14 | var1 at10 = 20 | var2 name = + [[Damage]] | var2 at0 = 8 | var2 at10 = 15 | var3 name = + Damage vs. [[Charr]] | var3 at0 = 7 | var3 at10 = 10}}
==Acquisition== '''[[Skill quest]]s''' *[[The Smell of Titan in the Morning]] (from [[Captain Langmar]] in [[Grothmar Wardowns]])
== Notes == * The bonus damage is [[Armor-ignoring]]. It does not affect other sources of Armor-ignoring damage but affects all forms of [[armor-respecting damage]], including direct-damage spells and skills as well as attacks, making this more effective than it first appears. * The bonus damage is dealt as long as the damage dealer remains standing in the ward; damage from ranged physical attacks as well as from [[area damage over time]] skills, such as [[Fire Storm]] or [[Spike Trap]], increases while the caster stands in the ward, and will decrease if they leave it. * The bonus damage is part of the original damage [[packet]] (e. g. [[Barbs]] and [[Mark of Pain]] will not trigger again on physical attacks).
