{{otheruses|the Ebon Vanguard rank skill|the skill used by Nola Sheppard|Ebon Vanguard Assassin Support (NPC)}} __NOTOC__{{Skill infobox | id = 2235 | name = Ebon Vanguard Assassin Support | campaign = Eye of the North | profession = | attribute = Ebon Vanguard rank | type = Spell | energy = 10 | activation = 1 | recharge = 30 | pve-only = y | causes1 = Summoned Creature | description = [[Spell]]. Summon a [[level]] {{gr2|14|20}} [[Ebon Vanguard Assassin]] that has [[Iron Palm]], [[Fox Fangs]], and [[Nine Tail Strike]]. This summoned Assassin [[Shadow Step]]s to [[target]] [[foe]]. If that foe is a [[Charr]], the Assassin lives for {{gr2|24|30}} seconds. If target foe is not a [[Charr]], the Assassin lives for {{gr2|12|15}} seconds. | concise description = Spell. Summon a level {{gr2|14|20}} assassin that has Iron Palm, Fox Fangs, and Nine Tail Strike; it Shadow Steps to this foe. If this foe is a Charr, the assassin lives for {{gr2|24|30}} seconds. If target foe is not a Charr, the Assassin lives for {{gr2|12|15}} seconds. | target = foes }}
{{skill progression max10| | title track = [[Ebon Vanguard rank]] | var1 name = Assassin [[level]] | var1 at0 = 14 | var1 at10 = 20 | var2 name = [[Duration]] (vs [[Charr]]) | var2 at0 = 24 | var2 at10 = 30 | var3 name = Duration (vs other foes) | var3 at0 = 12 | var3 at10 = 15 }}
==Acquisition== '''[[Skill quest]]s''' * [[Service: Practice, Dummy]] ([[Eye of the North (outpost)|Eye of the North]])
== Related skills == * {{Skill icon|Summon Ice Imp}} * {{Skill icon|Summon Mursaat}} * {{Skill icon|Summon Naga Shaman}} * {{Skill icon|Summon Ruby Djinn}}
== Notes ==
* When used against Charr, the [[Ebon Vanguard Assassin]] can survive long enough to complete up to two attack chains. When used against other foes, the Assassin only has enough time for a single attack chain. ** All its skills are [[Block|unblockable]] ** His [[Iron Palm]] will [[knock down]] foes that are [[hex]]ed or suffering from a [[condition]]. * You can create multiple Assassins in an area. * It is not [[Infusion|infused]] nor does it leave an exploitable [[corpse]]. * When its summoning period ends, it appears to Shadow Step into nothingness. * It will be higher than level 20 if cast under the effects of [[Signet of Illusions]] with an [[Illusion Magic]] rank 17 or more.
{{Anomaly|The Assassin doesn't shadow step; it is spawned directly next to the target.}} {{Anomaly|The Assassin is counted as a ''created'' creature for [[Spirit's Gift]], [[Explosive Growth]], and [[Boon of Creation]]. However, it does not count as a [[summoned creature]] and is not affected by [[Spawning Power]]. Despite this classification, it is not affected by [[Sulfurous Haze|sulfur]].}} {{Bug|Though the Assassin does not count towards the minion cap, summoning one will cause the game to check the players minion control limit, potentially destroying any minions over the limit.}} {{Anomaly|The Assassin does not always target the foe targeted by the caster, but instead targets the foe closest to its creation point.}} {{Bug| Very rarely, the assassin may survive indefinitely. This can occur if resurrected by an enemy-created [[Restoration]] spirit, as by [[Reborn Irukandji]].}}
== Trivia == *Assuming the Assassin is able to complete his combo, this summon has the highest consistent damage output among the five reputation-governed summons. *Contrary to the skill icon, the summoned Assassin ironically does not wear [[Ebon Vanguard armor]].

