{{Skill progression max10 |title track = [[Ebon Vanguard rank]] |var1 name = Piercing damage |var1 at0 = 54 |var1 at10 = 90 |var2 name = Additional piercing damage |var2 at0 = 540 |var2 at10 = 900 |var3 name = Bleeding [[duration]] |var3 at0 = 5 |var3 at10 = 25 }}
== Acquisition == '''[[Skill quest]]s''' * [[Falling Out]] (from [[Corpse of Brave Brent Poltroon]] in [[Dalada Uplands]])
== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Keiran's Sniper Shot (Hearts of the North)}}
== Trivia == * The [[skill icon]] is a male [[Ebon Vanguard]] [[Ranger]]. ** Based on events in [[Hearts of the North]] (and other sources), some believe that the sniper is [[Keiran Thackeray]] and that the icon is a small portrait of him. * When you successfully inflict the additional damage, one of a number of quotes appears in the [[chat window]]. Each is a reference to a movie, a game, and/or the [[w:Bible|Bible]]: ** ''"'''Snap! Headshot!'''"'' is a reference to ''"Boom Headshot!!,"'' a common phrase in many [[Wikipedia:first person shooter|first person shooter]] games. ** ''"'''One arrow one kill''',"'' is a reference to ''"One shot, one kill,"'' a phrase made popular in films that include snipers as important characters. ** ''"'''Balthazar bless my strength, teach my hands to war, and my fingers to fight''',"'' is a reference to the 144th Psalm in the Bible, which includes the phrase, ''"Blessed be the Lord, my strength, who teacheth my hands to war and my fingers to fight."'' Notably, the movie [[w:Saving Private Ryan|Saving Private Ryan]] includes a sniper who recites similar lines. ** ''"'''I am a Stone. I do not move. I do not tremble. I have no fear.'''"'' is a quotation from the movie [[w:Enemy at the Gates|Enemy at the Gates]], a World War II movie about snipers in the Battle of Stalingrad.

{{otheruses|the elite Mesmer skill|the skill type of the same name|Echo (skill type)}} __NOTOC__{{Skill infobox | id = 74 | name = Echo | campaign = Core | profession = Mesmer | type = Enchantment Spell | elite = yes | activation = 1 | recharge = 10 | energy = 5 | causes1 = Skill Copying | description = [[Elite]] [[Enchantment Spell]]. For 30 seconds, Echo is replaced with the next [[skill]] you use. Echo acts as this skill for 30 seconds. | concise description = Elite Enchantment Spell. (30 seconds.) Echo becomes the next skill you use (30 seconds). }}
== Acquisition == '''[[Signet of Capture]]''' * [[Prophecies]] ** [[Rwek Khawl Mawl]] ([[Perdition Rock]]) * [[Factions]] ** [[Mohby Windbeak]] ([[Gyala Hatchery (explorable area)]]) ** [[The Time Eater (boss)|The Time Eater]] ([[The Eternal Grove (explorable area)]]) * [[Nightfall]] ** [[Eshwe the Insane]] ([[Joko's Domain]])
== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Arcane Echo}}
== Notes== * Echo can copy powerful skills with long [[recharge time]]s, doubling the rate at which they can be used. * Use it to copy skills with short recharge times in order to [[spam]] them, e.g. [[adrenaline]] skills that have any recharge time. * Combine Echo with [[Arcane Echo]] to create [[Echo chain]]s, allowing you to have three copies of a skill at once. Add [[Arcane Mimicry]] to create multiple copies of a party member's [[elite]]. * Use [[Auspicious Incantation]] to help [[energy management|manage energy costs]] (especially since Echo chains consume a lot of energy); the downside is mitigated since the disabled skill gets replaced shortly after. * To capture Echo from a boss that has just copied a skill, wait 30 seconds (for the effect to wear off) before using your [[Signet of Capture]]. * If used to copy a [[Skill quick reference#Skills that are replaced with other skills|skill that can copy another skill or spell]], the copy [[duration]] of that skill is used and will bypass Echo's 30-second copy duration. ** E.g., if used to copy [[Arcane Larceny]]/[[Arcane Thievery|Thievery]] with Domination Magic rank 15, whatever spell that is stolen from a foe by the Echo version of Arcane Larceny/Thievery will remain as that stolen spell for 35 seconds and then revert back to Echo. ** E.g., if used to copy Arcane Larceny/Thievery with Domination Magic rank 0, whatever spell that is stolen from a foe by the Echo version of Arcane Larceny/Thievery will remain as that stolen spell for 5 seconds and then revert back to Echo. {{anomaly|Echo's description omits the fact that it cannot copy a Signet of Capture and itself.}}
== Trivia == * The [[skill icon]] has the same hand silhouette as [[Plague Touch]].
[[de:Echo]]

{{Skill infobox | id = 1271 | name = Echoing Banishment | recharge = 40 | campaign = Factions | special = Teleport monster | type = Shout | profession = Monster | target = foes | description = [[Shout]]. [[Target]] [[foe]] is banished to the mists and his spirit bound to Shiro. If the [[Bound spirit|Spirit Binder]] is destroyed, the spirit is freed. | concise description = Shout. Target foe is banished to the mists and his spirit bound to Shiro. If the Spirit Binder is destroyed, the spirit is freed.}}
== Related skills == * {{monster skill icon|Soul Vortex}}
== Notes == * This skill is used exclusively by [[Shiro Tagachi]] in the [[Imperial Sanctum]] mission. * This skill will summon a hostile [[Shiro'ken]] of the targeted character's primary [[profession]]{{verify|what about paragons and dervishes?}}. ** Destroying this shiroken will recharge skills akin to a [[Morale Boost]]. * Players targeted by this skill will be sent to an island directly north west of the island hosting the main battle against Shiro. ** Players will return to the main area upon death, entering the [[portal]] at the top of the island, or upon their party's successful defeat of the bound spirit that replaced them. ** The lighting of this island is similar to that of [[the Underworld]]. * Shiro will use this skill to banish party members with general guidelines: ** Heroes, pets, and other NPC [[ally|allies]] will never be banished. ** Players will only ever be banished if the party contains more than one player. ** Henchmen and players are banished in by ascending order of lowest-to-highest health. * Multiple players and henchmen can be banished at any given time, though only one banishment will occur with each usage of this skill. {{anomaly|Similar to Shiro's other skills, the descriptions do not mention that this skill cannot be [[disable]]d.}}
[[de:Widerhallende Verbannung]]

{{Skill infobox | id = 464 | name = Edge of Extinction | campaign = Prophecies | profession = Ranger | attribute = Beast Mastery | type = Nature Ritual | energy = 5 | activation = 5 | recharge = 60 | causes1 = Spirit | description = [[Nature Ritual]]. Create a level {{gr|1|10}} [[spirit]]. If a non-spirit [[creature]] within [[Spirit range|range]] [[Death|dies]], Edge of Extinction deals {{gr|14|50}} [[damage]] to all creatures of the same [[Creature type|type]] that are below 90% [[Health]] and within [[range]] of the spirit. This spirit dies after {{gr|30|150}} seconds. | concise description = Nature Ritual. Creates a level {{gr|1|10}} spirit ({{gr|30|150}} second lifespan). Deals {{gr|14|50}} damage to creatures in its range whenever a creature of the same type dies. Does not affect spirits. {{gray|No damage to creatures above 90% Health.}} | aoe = spirit }}
{{Skill progression |attribute = [[Beast Mastery]] |var1 name = [[Spirit]] level |var1 at0 = 1 |var1 at15 = 10 |var2 name = [[Damage]] |var2 at0 = 14 |var2 at15 = 50 |var3 name = [[Duration]] |var3 at0 = 30 |var3 at15 = 150}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Skill quest]]s''' * [[The Lost Princess]] ([[Fishermen's Haven]]) '''[[Skill trainer]]s''' * [[Bartoch]] ([[Droknar's Forge]]) * [[Dakk]] ([[Ember Light Camp]]) '''[[Signet of Capture]]''' * [[Sayad the Bloodless]] ([[Gates of Kryta]]) * [[Abijah the Decayed]] ([[D'Alessio Seaboard]]) * [[Dahr the Diseased]] ([[Nebo Terrace]]) * [[Ghita Bonz]] ([[Divinity Coast]], [[Majesty's Rest]])
== Notes == * This skill creates a [[Spirit of Extinction]]. * Beware of the possible backfire of this skill on your party or allied [[NPC]]s. ** [[M.O.X.]], [[Jora]], [[Pyre Fierceshot]], [[Ogden Stonehealer]], [[Vekk]] and [[Zhed Shadowhoof]] are respectively [[golem]], [[norn]], [[charr]], [[dwarf]], [[asura]] and [[centaur]] [[hero]]es. If using this skill, use those heroes rather than other human heroes of the same profession, as long as the area don't have other members of the same type (i.e. avoid [[Charr Homelands]] and [[Ascalon]] areas when using Pyre, [[Southern Shiverpeaks|Southern]] and [[Northern Shiverpeaks]] when using Ogden, and [[Maguuma Jungle]] when using Zhed; [[Avarr the Fallen]] and [[Johon the Oxflinger]] are the only norn foes you can kill). ** Not all allied human NPCs are considered the same creature type for the purposes of this ritual. For example, service NPCs (collectors, merchants, etc) and many non-hostile NPCs (including allies but not [[henchmen]] party members) each have their own species category separate from both each other and players. * This skill is particularly lethal to [[minion]]s, as most of them will already be below the 90% health requisite due to their innate [[health degeneration]]. * Consider using with disease, as it also affects members of the same type and allows to reach the 90% requisite more easily. * As with all nature rituals, being in range of 2 EoE spirits does not increase the damage - only the stronger EoE takes effect. :* If 2 creatures are each in range of a different EoE (and each other), the EoE that deals damage will be the one in range of the creature that died.
