__NOTOC__{{Skill infobox | id = 227 | name = Glimmering Mark | campaign = Prophecies | profession = Elementalist | attribute = Air Magic | type = Hex Spell | elite = y | energy = 10 | activation = 1 | recharge = 15 | causes1 = Blind | description = [[Elite]] [[Hex Spell]]. For 10 seconds, [[target]] [[foe]] and all foes [[adjacent]] to your target take {{gr|5|25}} [[damage]] each second. Foes using [[attack skill]]s are [[Blind]]ed for 3 seconds. This hex ends if you use a [[skill]] that targets this foe. | concise description = Elite Hex Spell. (10 seconds.) Deals {{gr|5|25}} damage each second to target and adjacent foes. Inflicts Blindness {{sic|Doesn't indicate Blindness duration}} on foes using attack skills. {{gray|Ends if you use a skill that targets this foe.}} | aoe = adjacent }}
{{Skill progression |attribute = [[Air Magic]] |var1 name = [[Armor-ignoring damage]] |var1 at0 = 5 |var1 at15 = 25}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Signet of Capture]]''' * [[Edibbo Kepkep]] ([[Talus Chute]] and [[Spearhead Peak]]) * [[Alana Kepkep]] ([[Witman's Folly]])
==Related skills== *{{skill icon|Illusion of Pain}} *{{skill icon|Renewing Surge}} *{{skill icon|Smoldering Embers}} *{{skill icon|Wastrel's Demise}}
== Notes == * Only skills which directly target the foe cause Glimmering Mark to end; the hex is unaffected by skills that might impact the target through [[area of effect]]s. * Blindness is applied before the attack skill hits. * Blindness is applied if an attack skill is being [[Activation time|activated]] when Glimmering Mark does damage. Carefully [[Attack speed|timed]] or quick attack skills can be activated between two damage [[packet]]s of Glimmering Mark, avoiding the Blindness effect.
====Hero usage==== Heroes using this skill will switch targets in most cases to avoid prematurely ending this skill (see discussion): *When attacked alone by the enemies *When engaging as a result of the player attacking *After being ordered to perform Glimmering Mark before combat *When locked onto a target, in which case Glimmering Mark was cast on another enemy
== Trivia == * This skill has changed since its introduction; see its [[Glimmering Mark/Skill history|skill history]] for details. {{Bug|The concise description fails to specify the duration of the Blind condition}}
