{{redirect 2|"GOE" and "GoE"|the other use|[[Glyph of Essence]]}} {{Skill infobox | id = 199 | name = Glyph of Energy | campaign = Prophecies | profession = Elementalist | attribute = Energy Storage | type = Glyph | energy = 5 | activation = 1 | recharge = 25 | elite = y | target = self | range = | aoe = | causes1 = Decreased Energy Cost | causes2 = Increased Attribute | description = [[Elite]] [[Glyph]]. Your next {{gr|1|3}} [[spell]][s] do[es] not cause [[Overcast]] and cost[s] {{gr|10|25}} less [[Energy]] to cast. Your elemental [[attribute]]s are increased by {{gr|1|2}}. | concise description = Elite Glyph. Your next {{gr|1|3}} spell[s] do[es] not cause Overcast and cost[s] {{gr|10|25}} less Energy. Gain {{gr|1|2}} to all elemental attributes. }}
{{Skill progression | attribute = [[Energy Storage]] | var1 name = [[Spell]]s affected | var1 at0 = 1 | var1 at15 = 3 | var2 name = [[Energy]] reduction | var2 at0 = 10 | var2 at15 = 25 | var3 name = [[Attribute]] increase | var3 at0 = 1 | var3 at15 = 2 }}
== Acquisition == '''[[Signet of Capture]]''' * [[Hyl Thunderwing]] ([[Mineral Springs]])
== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Elemental Attunement}} ([[elite]]) * {{skill icon|Elemental Lord}} * {{skill icon|Glyph of Elemental Power}} * {{skill icon|Glyph of Lesser Energy}} * {{skill icon|Master of Magic}} (elite)
== Notes == * Glyph of Energy only cancels the base overcast cost of the spells, not overcast caused by other sources. ** [[Arcane Languor]] and [[Iron Mist]] will still cause overcast on spells. ** [[Over the Limit]] will still generate passive overcast. ** [[Equinox]] and [[Sheer Exhaustion]] will not cause overcast. * Skills that let Glyph of Energy use its full potential are [[Maelstrom]], [[Meteor Shower]], [[Earthquake]], and its duplicate [[Dragon's Stomp]]. * A [[cancel]]led spell will still consume one use of the glyph. * Non-spell elemental skills (e.g. [[Lightning Touch]]) will take advantage of the bonus and ''will not'' count as a use of the glyph. * Any elemental attribute raised to at least 9 will trigger the bonus armor from [[Prismatic Insignia]]. * Has no [[duration]] (this is one of the few [[Upkeep#Skills that last indefinitely without an upkeep|skills that last indefinitely without an upkeep]]). {{hero|[[Hero]]es will only use expensive spells or spells that cause Overcast while under the effects of this glyph. ** If using the skill at high Energy Storage, using such skills with a low recharge time (e.g. [[Lightning Hammer]], [[Obsidian Flame]], [[Rodgort's Invocation]], and [[Vapor Blade]]) can help make full use of the big energy pool.}}
