== Notes == * Cripple is applied before the hit deals damage, which makes it useful to meet the condition of certain skills like [[Reap Impurities]]. * Condition transfer occurs after hitting the target, but before the [[weakness]] induced by [[Wearying Spear]]. ** If the user is affected by weakness, the attack skill that triggers the condition transfer will still be weakened. ** You also have to successfully hit in order to transfer a condition (unlike [[Assassin's Remedy]]), making it very unlikely to remove [[Blind]]ness. * A skill that changes your weapon [[damage type]] to [[cold damage]], like [[Grenth's Fingers]], counts as wielding a cold weapon. ** Conversely, any skill that changes damage type to something other than cold will prevent Grenth's Grasp from triggering. * Consider using with [[Volley]] for spammable mass cripple and condition transfer. [[Category:Skills named after eponymous NPCs]]
