{{Skill infobox | id = 2104 | name = Intensity | campaign = Nightfall | profession = Elementalist | attribute = Sunspear rank | pve-only = y | type = Skill | energy = 5 | activation | recharge = 10 | description = [[Skill (skill type)|Skill]]. For 10 seconds, the next time you deal [[elemental damage]] with a [[spell]] to a [[target]], you deal {{gr2|60|70}}% of that damage to all other [[foe]]s [[in the area]]. | concise description = Skill. (10 seconds.) The next time you deal elemental damage with a spell, other targets in the area take {{gr2|60|70}}% of that damage. | aoe = in the area | target = self }}
{{Skill progression max10 | title track = [[Sunspear rank]] | var1 name = % [[Damage]] | var1 at0 = 60 | var1 at10 = 70 }}
==Acquisition== '''[[Hero skill trainer]]s''' *[[Pikin]] ([[Kamadan, Jewel of Istan]]) *[[Shiloh]] ([[Sunspear Great Hall]]) *[[Libeh]] ([[Command Post]])
==Notes== *Intensity's [[area of effect]] damage triggers on one foe from the first elemental damage [[packet]] done by a spell after the activation of the skill. **High damage packets from spells such as [[Fireball]], [[Rodgort's Invocation]], [[Lightning Orb]], [[Lightning Surge]] or [[Lightning Hammer]] are usually better to optimize intensity's effect. **Try to target foes with the lowest armor rating, typically casters and foes affected with [[Cracked Armor]]. *The damage [[Armor-ignoring damage|ignores armor]]. *This skill can be activated while [[Movement|moving]] or [[Activation time|activating]] a [[skill]]; you can also use it ''after'' you cast the spell to be intensified if there is a delay between the end of the casting and the damage packet, e.g. [[Meteor Shower]] &rarr; Intensity. *Outside of elementalist skills, high elemental damage is mostly found in [[Death Magic]] ([[Deathly Swarm]] and [[Icy Veins]] being of note), and [[Spawning Power]]/[[Channeling Magic]] ([[Ancestor's Rage]], [[Rupture Soul]], [[Spirit Rift]] and [[Destructive was Glaive]] being of note).
{{bug|When sorting skills by campaign, this is listed under [[Core]] although it's a Nightfall skill.}}
==Trivia== *The functionality of this skill has changed since its introduction; see its [[Intensity/Skill history|skill history]] for details.
