{{Skill infobox | id = 538 | name = Invulnerability | campaign = Core | type = Skill | profession = Monster | special = Passive | description = [[Monster]] cannot be [[attack]]ed. | concise description = Monster cannot be attacked. }}
== Related skills == * {{Skill Icon|Aegis (PvP)}}
== Notes == * This skill is a passive, continuously active effect, making it invisible to players. It is used by various [[NPC]]s that are not supposed to be fought. * The description is misleading: This skill prevents others from targeting the NPC (with skills or attacks), gives them immunity to [[damage]] (including indirect damage, e.g. from [[AoE]] or reflective skills such as [[Retribution]]), and provides +20 [[health regeneration]] (that bypasses the normal +10 cap; the foe gains 40 health per second) ** Its targeting prevention also stops allies from being able to use beneficial skills on the immune NPC, e.g. allies could not use [[Orison of Healing]]. ** It does not prevent [[Life Stealing]] or the indirect damage from combining [[Illusionary Weaponry]] with skills such as [[Cyclone Axe]]. ** It is still possible to kill foes that carry this skill, although it is extremely difficult. *** There are various methods, most of which involve [[Spiritleech Aura]], [[Vengeful Was Khanhei]] and [[Vengeful Weapon]], [[hard mode]] (so that the foe has a high [[attack speed]]), and lots of energy.
== External links == * [http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pC0R8fNozdc One of many examples on YouTube] of players killing an ''invulnerable'' foe.

