__NOTOC__{{Skill infobox | id = 2212 | name = Light of Deldrimor | energy = 5 | activation = {{3/4}} | recharge = 20 | campaign = Eye of the North | attribute = Deldrimor rank | type = Spell | pve-only = y | causes1 = Holy Damage | description = [[Spell]]. All [[foe]]s [[in the area]] are struck for {{gr2|55|80}} [[holy damage]]. The location of hidden objects are [[Ping|briefly indicated]] on your [[Compass]]. Any hidden objects in the area are revealed. | concise description = Spell. Deals {{gr2|55|80}} holy damage to foes in the area. Pings hidden objects within the area on the compass. | aoe = in the area | target = untargeted | pbaoe = self }}
{{Skill progression max10 |title track = [[Deldrimor rank]] |var1 name = [[Holy damage]] |var1 at0 = 55 |var1 at10 = 80 }}
==Acquisition== '''[[Skill quest]]s''' *[[Destructive Research]] ([[Battledepths]] or [[Central Transfer Chamber]])
== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Heart of Holy Flame}} * {{skill icon|Zealous Renewal}}
==Notes== [[Image:LoD ball of light.jpg|right|thumbnail|The green shimmer that marks a hidden object.]]
* Hidden objects can only be found in [[dungeon]]s. ** There are no hidden objects in [[Fronis Irontoe's Lair]], [[Slavers' Exile]], or in any [[Depths of Tyria|underground]] instance entered as part of a [[primary quest]]. * Using the skill will expose any nearby hidden objects; any remaining ones within compass range will ''ping'' yellow on the compass and be marked by a green shimmer over its location. ** A yellow ping does not sound for the objects already shimmering. ** The shimmer remains for a short period of time. * Hidden objects include: ** Ghostly allies, i.e. a level 24 [[Dwarven Ghost]]. ** [[Hidden Treasure]]s. ** Secret passages, such as the wall in the first level of [[Raven's Point]] that crumbles once the players are in front of it. ** Switches that open doors. * The skill and the Hidden Treasures are commonly referred to as ''LoD''. * This skill is required to spawn the [[Silver Vaettir]].
== Trivia == * The [[Feedback:Game updates/20111103|November 3, 2011 game update]] fixed a [[bug]] that prevented hidden treasures from appearing under various circumstances, including failing to spawn if discovered shortly after entering a level or not discovered on first use of the skill. Some treasures never spawned. Since the fix, ''all'' possible treasures now spawn; for example, now you can find around 10 treasures on the third level of [[Oola's Lab]] compared to typically finding only five or six in the past. {{gw2w}}
