__NOTOC__{{Skill infobox | id = 230 | name = Lightning Javelin | campaign = Prophecies | profession = Elementalist | attribute = Air Magic | type = Spell | energy = 5 | recharge = 5 | activation = 1 | target = foes | range = Casting | aoe = linear | causes1 = Lightning Damage | causes2 = Interrupt | causes3 = Armor Penetration | description = [[Spell]]. Send out a [[Projectile spell|Lightning Javelin]] that strikes for {{gr|15|50}} [[lightning damage]] if it hits. Lightning Javelin [[interrupt]]s [[attack]]ing [[foe]]s. This spell has 25% [[armor penetration]] and strikes all foes between you and your [[target]]. | concise description = Spell. Projectile: Deals {{gr|15|50}} lightning damage. Interrupts if your target is attacking. 25% armor penetration. Strikes all foes between you and your target. }}
{{Skill progression |attribute = [[Air Magic]] |var1 name = [[Lightning damage]] |var1 at0 = 15 |var1 at15 = 50}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Skill quest]]s''' * [[The Supremacy of Air]] ([[Foible's Fair]] - [[Ascalon (pre-Searing)|pre-Searing]]) '''[[Skill trainer]]s''' * [[Halbrik]] ([[Ascalon City (outpost)|Ascalon City]] - pre-Searing) * [[Sir Bertran]] ([[Ascalon City]]) * [[Dakk]] ([[Ember Light Camp]])
== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Signet of Clumsiness}} * {{skill icon|Spear of Light}}
== Notes == * [[Hero]]es do not use this skill on non-attacking foes. * Lightning Javelin uses a unique area of effect. ** The projectile is identical to a [[staff]]'s attack, and follows a high arc, similar to that of a [[flatbow]]. ** The projectile strikes foes [[adjacent]] to the target, and all foes adjacent to the projectile's flight-path originating from the caster. ** The projectile seemingly acknowledges "facing", as it does not affect "flanking" adjacent foes' immediate position to the caster's "left/right sides and rear", when facing relative to the target; despite the area of effect being centered on the caster. ** If the target foe evades towards the spell caster and the projectile misses far, the targeted foe will not receive any damage even if they are still in the projectiles flight path. This is commonly seen using lightning javelin to engage a fight with npcs.
== Trivia == * The [[functionality]] of this skill has changed since its introduction; see its [[Lightning Javelin/Skill history|skill history]] for details.
