== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Animate Bone Horror}} * {{skill icon|Aura of the Lich}} ([[elite]]) * {{skill icon|Defile Flesh}} * {{skill icon|Lingering Curse}} (elite) * {{skill icon|Mark of Death}}
== Notes == * The spell requires the target to leave an exploitable [[corpse]]; but does ''not'' exploit the corpse. * Combine with [[Deep Wound]] or [[Lingering Curse]] to exactly reach the -40% [[Effect stacking#Effects|healing modification cap]]. * [[Verata's Gaze]] can be used to gain control of the masterless Bone Horror. ** Alternatively, if you do not intend to take control of the minion, [[Swap]] can be used to shadow step it away from your team (preferably in the opposing team). It also provides a suitable target to trigger the bonus effects of [[Holy Spear]]. * Heroes tend to spam this skill regardless of whether the target or enemy group has healing skills, leading to several extra Bone Horrors per fight. * Since the Bone Horror is created masterless, it will not trigger skills that depend on [[Summoned creature#Skills that trigger by summoning creatures|summoned creature creation]] such as [[Boon of Creation]]. {{anomaly|Cannot be used on non-[[fleshy]] targets.}}
== Trivia == * Possibly meant to be an "evil" version of the [[Monk]] skill {{skill icon|Divine Intervention}}, which similarly triggers on death. == See also == * [[List of minion skills]]
