{{otheruses|the skill Master of Magic|the NPC on the [[Isle of the Nameless]]|Master of Magic (NPC)}} {{Skill infobox | name = Master of Magic | id = 1378 | campaign = Nightfall | profession = Elementalist | attribute = Energy Storage | type = Enchantment Spell | elite = y | energy = 5 | activation = 1 | recharge = 10 | causes1 = Increased Attribute | causes2 = Energy Gain | description = [[Elite]] [[Enchantment Spell]]. For {{gr|1|61}} second[s], all of your elemental [[attribute]]s are set to {{gr|8|14}} and your elemental [[spell]]s return 30% of their [[Energy]] cost. | concise description = Elite Enchantment Spell. ({{gr|1|61}} second[s]). Your elemental attributes are set to {{gr|8|14}} and elemental spells return 30% of their Energy cost. | target = untargeted }}
{{Skill progression |attribute = [[Energy Storage]] |var1 name = [[Duration]] |var1 at0 = 1 |var1 at15 = 61 |var2 name = [[Attribute]] rank |var2 at0 = 8 |var2 at15 = 14}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Signet of Capture]]''' * [[Captain Mwende]] ([[Consulate Docks]]) * [[Admiral Kantoh]] ([[Jahai Bluffs]]) * [[Captain Nebo]] ([[Pogahn Passage]]) * [[Hajok Earthguardian (Insect)]] ([[Yatendi Canyons]])
== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Elemental Attunement}} ([[elite]]) * {{skill icon|Elemental Lord}} * {{skill icon|Glyph of Elemental Power}} * {{skill icon|Glyph of Energy}} (elite)
== Notes == * This skill overrides any ''existing'' modifiers, including: skills that boost elemental attributes (e.g. [[Elemental Lord]]), [[rune]]s, [[Weakness]] and [[consumable]]s (e.g. [[Candy Corn]]). ** Bonuses will take effect if they are applied ''after'' Master of Magic (e.g. remove/reapply headgear before casting). ***Removing and reapplying runes has no effect. ** Renewing Master of Magic whilst under the attribute boosting modifiers will retain the higher attribute ranks and not reset them to the rank predicted by Master of Magic. * [[Journey to the North]] takes precedence, setting only one attribute to 12 (and any others to 9). {{verify|any/all of this might have changed}} * The most effective uses of this skill are: ** To boost the effectiveness of low-[[level]] [[character]]s, since it can allow to reach and maintain an elemental attribute rank of 9 at only rank 3 in energy storage. ** To maximize the strength of [[Prismatic Insignia]] (raising an elementalist's armor by 20). ** To free attribute points for [[build]]s that draw on several elementalist attributes or to meet the requirement of certain [[weapons]] (notably [[shield]]s). * The amount of energy regained is rounded down: 5 energy spells return 1 energy, 15 energy spells return 4 and 25 energy spells return 7. {{bug| While under the effects of Master of Magic, being [[weakness|weakened]] with attribute points in elemental ranks will cause elemental ranks to lower by 1. Elemental attributes without attribute points in will not lower by 1. }}
== Trivia == * The staff being held by the figure in the [[skill icon]] appears to be an [[Accursed Staff]]. * [[w:Master of Magic|Master of Magic]] was a best-selling strategy game published by MicroProse on 3.5" floppy disks in 1994.
