{{Skill infobox | id = 1276, 1316 | name = Meditation of the Reaper | campaign = Factions | special = Monster | type = Skill | recharge = 60 | target = self | description = [[Skill (skill type)|Skill]]. For 30 seconds, Shiro meditates and absorbs the next 500 [[damage]]. When this skill ends, Shiro [[Life stealing|steals]] 20 [[Health]] from all [[foe]]s for each second this skill was active. | concise description = Skill. (30 seconds.) Shiro meditates and absorbs the next 500 damage. When this skill ends, Shiro steals 20 Health from all foes for each second this skill was active. | aoe = party }}
== Related skills == * {{monster skill icon|Nightmare Refuge}}
== Notes == * This is a monster skill used by [[Shiro Tagachi]] when he is at approximately 75% health or below. * When this skill is used, it is applied to all [[party]] members within compass [[range]] (i.e. it appears in each party member's [[effects monitor]]). * While this skill is active, Shiro does not [[attack]], move nor use any [[skill]]s. * To end this skill early, 500 damage has to be "dealt" to Shiro. While damage is [[Damage reduction|reduced]] to 0, dealing what would have been 500 will end the skill early. * As [[health degeneration]], [[health loss]], and [[life stealing]] are not considered damage, Shiro can still be harmed by these while this skill is active. * When this skill ends, Shiro will steal health from all allies within [[spirit range]] regardless if they have this skill in their effects monitor (e.g. [[summoning stone]] allies or [[spirit]]s created after this skill was used and is active). {{ bug|On rare occasions, Shiro will remain in his "meditation" even after taking more than 500 damage. He will remain that way for the rest of this mission, but will take damage after the initial 500.}} {{ anomaly|Similar to Shiro's other skills, the descriptions do not mention that this skill cannot be [[disable]]d.}}
