{{skill infobox | name = Metamorphosis | campaign = Eye of the North | special = Monster | type = Skill | elite = n | recharge = 9,999 | description = [[Skill (skill type)|Skill]]. Creature changes into an adult [[krait]]. | concise description = Skill. Creature changes into an adult krait. }}
==Notes== *This skill is used by [[Krait Neoss]]. *This skill causes the Krait to vanish after several seconds, [[spawn]]ing a [[Krait]] [[Krait Devouss|Devouss]], [[Krait Necross|Necross]], [[Krait Hypnoss|Hypnoss]] or [[Krait Arcanoss|Arcanoss]]. The new Krait will be level 20 to 24 in normal mode and 26 in hard mode, and will yield loot, experience, count towards bounties - as will the original Krait if it is killed before vanishing. However, killing the Neoss before it disappears will not stop the new one from spawning. *The metamorphosis will count as [[death]], triggering skills like [[Assassin's Promise]]. * You can take advantage of this skill to divide their groups. New Kraits created by this skill will aid any other Kraits they see around, but are not part of their old group, so if you [[pull]] Krait far away from their spot, those that stay behind to transform will break [[aggro]] and forget about your [[party]], staying behind. This way, a party of 6 Krait Neoss can be divided into a group of 2...4 that followed you and 4...2 separate evolved Krait that you may manage to fight separately.
==Trivia== * This skill's stated recharge time is equivalent to just over 2¾ hours, which is the longest recharge time of any skill in the game. {{bug|Due to how ''Guild Wars'' stores recharge time, this skill recharges in [[w:Integer_(computer_science)#Short_integer|65,535]] [[wiktionary:centisecond|centiseconds]], (just over 10 minutes and 55 seconds), rather than the stated duration.}}
[[Category:Recharge time skills]]
[[de:Metamorphose]]

__NOTOC__{{Skill infobox | id = 192 | name = Meteor Shower | campaign = Prophecies | profession = Elementalist | attribute = Fire Magic | type = Spell | energy = 25 | recharge = 60 | activation = 5 | overcast = 10 | target = foes | range = Casting | aoe = adjacent | causes1 = Fire Damage | causes2 = Knockdown | description = [[Spell]]. Create a Meteor Shower at [[target]] [[foe]]'s location. For 9 seconds, foes [[adjacent]] to that location are struck for {{gr|7|112}} [[fire damage]] and [[knock down|knocked down]] every 3 seconds. | concise description = Spell. Deals {{gr|7|112}} fire damage and causes knock-down every 3 seconds (9 seconds). Hits foes adjacent to target's initial location. }}
{{Skill progression | attribute = [[Fire Magic]] | var1 name = [[Fire damage]] | var1 at0 = 7 | var1 at15 = 112 }}
== Acquisition == '''[[Skill trainer]]s''' * [[Captain Greywind]] ([[North Kryta Province]]) * [[Master Scout Kiera]] ([[Henge of Denravi]]) * [[Dakk]] ([[Ember Light Camp]])
== Related skills == * {{Skill icon|Maelstrom}} * {{Skill icon|Meteor}}
== Notes == * Although there is immediate visual indication of rocks hitting the ground, the first damage and [[knock down]] event does not occur until 3 seconds after the spell has been cast. ** Since the earliest knock down occurs after the first 3 seconds, it is recommended that foes are [[Snare_(tactic)|snared]] when the spell is cast. * If knock down length is increased to 3 seconds (from [[Earthbind]] or a [[Stonefist Insignia]]), then foes will either be knocked down two times with a 3 second delay, two times with a perfect [[quarterknock]], or three times with two perfect quarterknocks. * This is one of the few spells that makes full use of [[Glyph of Energy]]. * Be wary of foes using this skill against your party, especially if it is composed of mostly [[henchmen]] and [[hero]]es, as they will all stand in approximately the range of the attack (unless you order them to move), devastating your party.
== Trivia == * The [[skill icon]] is featured in the Series 2 [[Skill Pin]] set.

