{{Skill infobox | id = 795 | name = Nightmare Weapon | campaign = Factions | profession = Ritualist | attribute = Channeling Magic | type = Weapon Spell | energy = 5 | activation = 1 | recharge = 10 | causes1 = Life Stealing | description = [[Weapon Spell]]. For 12 seconds, [[target]] [[ally]] has a Nightmare Weapon. Target ally's next 3 [[attack]]s are reduced by {{gr|10|50}} [[damage]] and [[Life stealing|steal]] up to {{gr|10|50}} [[Health]]. | concise description = Weapon Spell. (12 seconds.) Target ally's attacks steal {{gr|10|50}} Health but deal {{gr|10|50}} less damage. {{gray|Ends after 3 attacks.}} | target = allies }}
{{Skill progression | attribute = [[Channeling Magic]] | maximum = 19 | var1 name = [[Damage reduction]] | var1 at0 = 10 | var1 at15 = 50 | var2 name = [[Life stealing]] | var2 at0 = 10 | var2 at15 = 50}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Skill trainer]]s''' * [[Yokuni]] ([[Maatu Keep]])<!--[[File:Yokuni can unlock Nightmare Weapon.jpg]]--> * [[Ossian]] ([[Cavalon]]) * [[Zytka]] ([[House zu Heltzer]]) * [[Zenaida]] ([[Harvest Temple]]) '''[[Signet of Capture]]''' * [[The Afflicted Mei]] ([[Dragon's Throat]])
== Related skills == *{{skill icon|Grenth's Aura}}
== Notes == * The amount of life stolen is not affected by the amount of damage you would have dealt. ** As a result, consider using this skill on allies that deal the ''least'' amount of attack damage if you want to minimize Nightmare Weapon's damage reduction. * Every hit is counted, but [[miss]]es are not. For example, if a [[Barrage]] attack successfully strikes two foes, but misses four others, Nightmare Weapon would only lose two charges. * Consider using with [[Dual Shot]] (commonly used in conjunction with [[Distracting Shot]]) and particularly [[Triple Shot]] for a [[spike]].
== Trivia == * The functionality of this skill has changed since its introduction; see its [[{{PAGENAME}}/Skill history|skill revision history]] for details.

