{{Skill infobox | id = 99 | name = Parasitic Bond | campaign = Core | profession = Necromancer | attribute = Curses | type = Hex Spell | energy = 5 | activation = 1 | recharge = 2 | causes1 = Health Degeneration | causes2 = Healing | description = [[Hex Spell]]. For 20 seconds, [[target]] [[foe]] suffers -1 [[Health degeneration]]. The caster is [[heal]]ed for {{gr|30|120}} when Parasitic Bond ends. | concise description = Hex Spell. (20 seconds.) Causes -1 Health degeneration. End effect: you are healed for {{gr|30|120}} Health. }}
{{Skill progression |attribute = [[Curses]] |var1 name = [[Heal]]ing |var1 at0 = 30 |var1 at15 = 120}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Skill quest]]s''' * [[Prophecies]] ** [[Oberan's Rage]] ([[Sardelac Sanitarium]]) '''[[Skill trainer]]s''' * Prophecies ** [[Captain Osric]] ([[Yak's Bend]]) ** [[Dakk]] ([[Ember Light Camp]]) * [[Factions]] ** [[Masaharu]] ([[Seitung Harbor]]) ** [[Michiko]] ([[Kaineng City]]) * [[Nightfall]] ** [[Tohn]] ([[Kamadan, Jewel of Istan]]) '''[[Hero skill trainer]]s''' * Nightfall ** [[Shiloh]] ([[Sunspear Great Hall]]) * [[Eye of the North]] ** [[Gedrel of Ascalon]] ([[Eye of the North (outpost)|Eye of the North]]) ** [[Kodan]] ([[Gunnar's Hold]]) ** [[Tyr the Skaald]] (Gunnar's Hold) ** [[Lexx]] ([[Rata Sum]])
== Notes == * This skill will end prematurely if the caster [[Death|dies]]. * This skill works effectively as a [[cover]] hex due to is low energy cost, cool down, and fixed duration. The healing notably provides a visual cue to the user when it is removed. * It is best not to remove Parasitic Bond if it is the only hex you or an ally is suffering from, because of numerous factors: the health degeneration it causes is negligible, removing it will heal the caster, it can be reapplied once it is removed due to its short recharge time, and it will end automatically once the caster [[Death|dies]] anyway. *If you cast this skill on a target which an ally has already put Parasitic Bond on, you will gain two [[packet]]s of healing. One for when theirs would have normally ended, and one when yours ends.
