{{Skill infobox | id = 5 | name = Power Block | campaign = Prophecies | profession = Mesmer | attribute = Domination Magic | type = Spell | elite = y | energy = 15 | activation = {{1/4}} | recharge = 20 | causes1= Disable | causes2= Interrupt | description = [[Elite]] [[Spell]]. If [[target]] [[foe]] is casting a [[spell]] or [[chant]], that [[skill]] and all skills of the same [[attribute]] are [[disable]]d for {{gr|1|12}} seconds and that skill is [[interrupt]]ed. | concise description = Elite Spell. If target foe is casting a spell or chant, that skill and all skills of the same attribute are disabled ({{gr|1|12}} seconds) and that skill is interrupted. }}
{{Skill progression | attribute = [[Domination Magic]] | var1 name = [[Disable]]d [[duration]] | var1 at0 = 1 | var1 at15 = 12}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Signet of Capture]]''' * [[Prophecies]] ** [[Lyssa's Cursed]] ([[Perdition Rock]]) ** [[Justiciar Sevaan]] ([[Divinity Coast (explorable area)]], during [[War in Kryta]]) * [[Guild Wars Eye of the North | Eye of the North]] ** [[Anmat the Trickster]] ([[Against the Charr]] and [[Sacnoth Valley]]) ** [[Faze Magekiller]] ([[Cathedral of Flames]])
== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Blackout}} * {{skill icon|Complicate}} * {{skill icon|Power Lock}}
== Notes == * If Power Block interrupts a [[PvE-only skill]] or one without a linked attribute, ''only'' that skill will be disabled; the target will still be able to use other title-track or [[no attribute]] skills. * [[Wastrel's Worry]] and [[Wastrel's Demise]] are good sources of unconditional damage during the period that Power Block disables skills, especially against single-attribute builds (e.g. [[nuker]]s). * Power Block will extend the recharge time of skills with a shorter disable/recharge time (skills with a longer downtime will not be affected). * Disables skills even if interruption is prevented.
