{{Skill infobox | id = 469 | name = Primal Echoes | campaign = Core | profession = Ranger | attribute = Beast Mastery | type = Nature Ritual | energy = 5 | recharge = 60 | activation = 5 | causes1 = Spirit | causes2 = Increased Energy Cost | description = [[Nature Ritual]]. Create a level {{gr|1|10}} [[Spirit]]. For non-Spirit creatures within its [[Spirit range|range]], [[Signet]]s cost 10 [[Energy]] to use. This Spirit dies after {{gr|30|150}} seconds. | concise description = Nature Ritual. Creates a level {{gr|1|10}} spirit ({{gr|30|150}} second lifespan). Signets cost 10 energy for creatures in range. Does not affect spirits. | aoe = spirit }}
{{Skill progression | attribute = [[Beast Mastery]] | var1 name = [[Spirit]] [[level]] | var1 at0 = 1 | var1 at15 = 10 | var2 name = '''Spirit''' [[duration]] | var2 at0 = 30 | var2 at15 = 150 }}
== Acquisition == '''[[Skill trainer]]s''' * [[Prophecies]] ** [[Gammel]] ([[Copperhammer Mines]]) ** [[Dakk]] ([[Ember Light Camp]]) * [[Factions]] ** [[Michiko]] ([[Kaineng Center]]) ** [[Akane]] ([[Senji's Corner]]) * [[Nightfall]] ** [[Zendeht]] ([[Gate of Torment]]) '''[[Signet of Capture]]''' * [[Prophecies]] ** [[Henge Guardian]] ([[Aurora Glade]]) ** [[Ruinwing]] ([[Riverside Province]]) ** [[Bone Dragon (boss)|Bone Dragon]] ([[Sanctum Cay]])
== Notes == * This skill creates a [[Spirit of Primal Echoes]]. * The effects of this skill are applied before the energy modifiers from [[Quickening Zephyr]] or [[Energizing Wind]]. * [[Expertise]] will reduce the increased cost of ranger signets. * This skill often ruins [[bonder]]s who use [[Blessed Signet]] for energy management.

__NOTOC__ {{Skill infobox | id = 831 | name = Primal Rage | campaign = Factions | profession = Warrior | attribute = Strength | type = Stance | elite = y | adrenaline = 4 | recharge = 10 | causes1 = Increased Attack Speed | causes2 = Increased Movement Speed | description = [[Elite]] [[Stance]]. For {{gr|1|15}} second[s], you [[Attack speed|attack 33% faster]] and [[Speed boost|move 25% faster]], but you take double [[damage]]. | concise description = Elite Stance. ({{gr|1|15}} second[s].) You attack 33% faster and move 25% faster. {{gray|You take double damage.}} }}
{{Skill progression | attribute = [[Strength]] | var1 name = [[Duration]] | var1 at0 = 1 | var1 at15 = 15}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Signet of Capture]]''' * [[Strongroot Tanglebranch]] ([[Morostav Trail]]) * [[Reefclaw Ragebound]] ([[Gyala Hatchery (explorable area)]])
== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Drunken Master}} * {{skill icon|Frenzy}} * {{skill icon|Rampage as One}} ([[elite]]) * {{skill icon|Soldier's Fury}} (elite) * {{skill icon|Onslaught}} (elite)
== Notes == *[[Damage reduction]], such as [[Protective Spirit]], will be taken into account after Primal Rage, therefore mitigating the double damage. **If not using skills such as Protective Spirit, the use of a [[cancel stance]] is advisable. * If playing PvE with a high rank in the [[Deldrimor]] title, consider bringing [[Drunken Master]] over Primal Rage since it provides a good [[IAS]] and [[IMS]] without any drawback. This is especially true if using [[alcohol]], as the two boosts will be respectively equal and higher than those provided by Primal Rage.
== Trivia == * [[w:Primal Rage|Primal Rage]] is the name of a 1994 video game.
