__NOTOC__ {{Skill infobox | id = 432 | name = Read the Wind | campaign = Core | profession = Ranger | attribute = Marksmanship | type = Preparation | energy = 5 | recharge = 12 | activation = 2 | has-pvp = y | causes1 = Increased Projectile Speed | description = [[Preparation]]. For 24 seconds, your arrows move twice as fast and deal {{gr|3|10}} extra [[damage]]. | concise description = Preparation. (24 seconds). +{{gr|3|10}} damage. Your arrows move twice as fast. }}
{{Skill progression | attribute = [[Marksmanship]] | var1 name = + [[Damage]] | var1 at0 = 3 | var1 at15 = 10}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Skill quest]]s''' * [[Prophecies]] ** [[A Test of Marksmanship]] ([[Regent Valley (pre-Searing)|Regent Valley]] - [[Ascalon (pre-Searing)|pre-Searing]]) * [[Factions]] ** [[The Yeti Hunt]] ([[Kinya Province]]) '''[[Skill trainer]]s''' * Prophecies ** [[Halbrik]] ([[Ascalon City (outpost)|Ascalon City]] - pre-Searing) ** [[Sir Bertran]] ([[Ascalon City]]) ** [[Dakk]] ([[Ember Light Camp]]) * Factions ** [[Masaharu]] ([[Seitung Harbor]]) ** [[Michiko]] ([[Kaineng Center]]) '''[[Hero skill trainer]]s''' * Nightfall ** [[Libeh]] ([[Command Post]]) '''[[Profession changer]]s''' * [[Core]] ** [[Profession Changer (NPC)|Profession Changer]] ([[Great Temple of Balthazar]]) * Factions ** [[Senji]] ([[Senji's Corner]]) * Nightfall ** [[Zuwarah]] ([[Command Post]])
== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Favorable Winds}}
== Notes ==
* This skill sets a single flight time and arc for standard arrows fired from any [[bow]]: ** All standard arrows travel at the same (faster) rate and fly nearly parallel to the ground. ** Bow attack skills benefit from the bonus damage, but follow the original time and arc, e.g. [[Broad Head Arrow]] travels more slowly, [[Quick Shot]] moves twice as fast as the default for the bow. [[Arcing Shot]] is an exception to this; its arc is greatly reduced.
* When this preparation is used near a [[Favorable Winds]] spirit, the bonus damage stacks, but the speed does not (i.e. arrows still move twice as fast). ** Read the Wind is a slightly better choice for [[Flatbow]]s, since the lowered arc makes it less likely that [[foe]]s will [[dodge]].
