__NOTOC__{{Skill infobox | id = 925 | name = Recall | campaign = Factions | profession = Assassin | type = Enchantment Spell | energy = 15 | activation = 1 | recharge = 10 | upkeep = -1 | causes1 = Shadow Step | causes2 = Disable | description = [[Enchantment Spell]]. While you [[Upkeep|maintain]] Recall, nothing happens. When Recall ends, you [[Shadow Step]] to the [[ally]] you [[target]]ed when you activated this [[skill]] and all of your skills are [[disable]]d for 10 seconds. | concise description = Enchantment Spell. End effect: Shadow Step to target ally. {{gray|Cannot self-target and disables all of your skills for 10 seconds when it ends.}} | target = other allies }}
== Acquisition == '''[[Skill trainer]]s''' * [[Masaharu]] ([[Seitung Harbor]]) * [[Michiko]] ([[Kaineng Center]]) * [[Ziinyingmao Kaga]] ([[Dragon's Throat (outpost)|Dragon's Throat]]) * [[Zytka]] ([[House zu Heltzer]])
== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Aura of Displacement}} ([[elite]]) * {{skill icon|Shadow Meld}} (elite)
== Notes == * The enchantment is maintained on the caster, not the targeted ally. ** If the target dies, you will continue to maintain Recall. ** If you dismiss the enchantment while the target is dead, you will not shadow step nor will your skills be disabled. Once the target is resurrected, the skill will resume its normal function. ** If you die while maintaining Recall your corpse will not shadow step. * You will step to the target if the enchantment ends because you and the target move out of [[compass range]] from each other. {{anomaly|The full description does not state that this skill cannot self-target.}}
==Trivia== *Recall is the only compass range shadow step-skill that does not [[teleport]] you back to a previous position.

__NOTOC__ {{Skill infobox | id = 834 | name = Reckless Haste | campaign = Factions | profession = Necromancer | attribute = Curses | type = Hex Spell | energy = 15 | activation = 1 | recharge = 12 | causes1 = Miss | causes2 = Increased Attack Speed | description = [[Hex Spell]]. For {{gr|6|12}} seconds, [[target]] [[foe]] and all [[adjacent]] foes are hexed with Reckless Haste. While hexed, they [[Attack speed|attack 25% faster]] but have a 50% chance to [[miss]] with [[attack]]s. | concise description = Hex Spell. Also hexes foes adjacent to your target ({{gr|6|12}} seconds). These foes have 50% chance to miss, but attack 25% faster. | aoe = adjacent }}
{{Skill progression | attribute = [[Curses]] | var1 name = [[Duration]] | var1 at0 = 6 | var1 at15 = 12}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Skill trainer]]s''' * [[Michiko]] ([[Kaineng Center]]) * [[Akane]] ([[Senji's Corner]]) * [[Nicodemus]] ([[Leviathan Pits]])
== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Blurred Vision}} * {{skill icon|Price of Failure}} * {{skill icon|Spirit of Failure}}
== Notes == * As a result of this hex, target foe's raw [[damage]] output is expected to decrease by 33%. * Similarly to blocking, hexes that cause misses combine multiplicatively and not additively. Thus, a foe hexed with both Reckless Haste and [[Price of Failure]] has a 62.5% chance to miss with attacks. * Good synergy with skills like [[Spiteful Spirit]] and [[Empathy]] in [[Normal mode]]; the increased attack speed will trigger these more often. * This skill will not increase [[mob]]s' attack speed in [[Hard mode]] because they are already at the attack speed cap; however, it will still cause them to miss.
== Trivia == * The [[skill icon]] is similar to [[Images of Remorse]].

