{{Skill progression |attribute = Restoration Magic |var1 name = [[Spirit]] level |var1 at0 = 1 |var1 at15 = 20 |var2 name = [[Party healing|Heal]]/second-[[Health loss|loss]]/member |var2 at0 = 3 |var2 at15 = 10 |var3 name = Spirit [[duration]] |var3 at0 = 30 |var3 at15 = 90 }}
== Acquisition == '''[[Skill trainer]]s''' * [[Micah Fergson]] ([[Eye of the North (outpost)|Eye of the North]]) * [[Sida]] ([[Gunnar's Hold]]) * [[Ybbob]] ([[Rata Sum]]) '''[[Hero skill trainer]]s''' * [[Gedrel of Ascalon]] (Eye of the North) * [[Kodan]] (Gunnar's Hold) * [[Tyr the Skaald]] (Gunnar's Hold) * [[Lexx]] (Rata Sum)
==Related skills== *{{skill icon|Agony}}
== Notes == * This skill creates a [[Spirit of Rejuvenation]]. * The spirit is created with a higher level than other spirits at the same attribute rank. At 21 Restoration Magic, it is level 28, which is the highest leveled summoned spirit in the game. * Only heals party members below full health, so while your party hasn't started combat, try not to equip [[vampiric]] weapon modifiers. * At level 14 (0 [[Spawning Power]]), Rejuvenation does the equivalent of 5 [[pip]]s of [[health regeneration]] for a total of 38 seconds distributed amongst the party members (1 party member under its effect will receive 38 seconds while 4 party members will receive 9.5 seconds, etc.).
== Trivia == * The functionality of this skill has changed since its introduction; see its [[/Skill history|skill revision history]] for details.
