{{redirect 2|"RoF"|the Prophecies mission|[[Ring of Fire]]}} {{Skill infobox | id = 307 | name = Reversal of Fortune | campaign = Core | profession = Monk | attribute = Protection Prayers | type = Enchantment Spell | energy = 5 | recharge = 2 | activation = {{1/4}} | causes1 = Damage Reduction | causes2 = Healing | description = [[Enchantment Spell]]. For 8 seconds, the next time [[target]] [[ally]] would take [[damage]] or [[Life stealing|life steal]], that ally gains that amount of [[Health]] instead, maximum {{gr|15|80}}. | concise description = Enchantment Spell. (8 seconds.) Converts the next incoming damage or life steal (maximum {{gr|15|80}}) to healing. | target = allies }}
{{Skill progression | attribute = [[Protection Prayers]] | var1 name = Maximum [[heal]]ing | var1 at0 = 15 | var1 at15 = 80}} {{TOCright}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Skill quest]]s''' * [[Prophecies]] ** [[Protection Prayers (quest)|Protection Prayers]] ([[Green Hills County]] - [[Ascalon (pre-Searing)|pre-Searing]]) * [[Factions]] ** [[Stale Mate]] ([[Sunqua Vale]]) * [[Nightfall]] ** [[Primary Training]] ([[Churrhir Fields]]) ** [[Choose Your Secondary Profession (Nightfall quest)|Choose Your Secondary Profession]] (Churrhir Fields) '''[[Skill trainer]]s''' * Prophecies ** [[Halbrik]] ([[Ascalon City (outpost)|Ascalon City]] - pre-Searing) ** [[Sir Bertran]] ([[Ascalon City]]) ** [[Dakk]] ([[Ember Light Camp]]) '''[[Profession changer]]s''' * [[Core]] ** [[Profession Changer (NPC)|Profession Changer]] ([[Great Temple of Balthazar]]) * Factions ** [[Senji]] ([[Senji's Corner]]) * Nightfall ** [[Zuwarah]] ([[Command Post]])
== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Life Sheath}} ([[elite]]) * {{skill icon|Mark of Protection}} (elite) * {{skill icon|Reversal of Damage}} * {{skill icon|Vengeful Weapon}} * {{skill icon|Weapon of Remedy}} (elite) * {{skill icon|Xinrae's Weapon}} (elite)
== Notes == * Just like the concise description says, this spell converts damage to healing, up to the stated maximum. For example, at rank 12 it can negate up to 134 damage (67 damage reduced and 67 damage healed). * This spell heals you before you take any damage above its conversion limit. This can save a low-health target, but it will also result in a net health loss if a full health target takes damage above its conversion limit. * This skill, unlike Reversal of Damage, will trigger ''after'' damage reduction like [[Protective Spirit]] and [[Protective Bond]], meaning that you often won't get the full benefit from this skill with other protection in place.
{{Outdated info|}} ;[[Feedback:Game updates/20190205|February 05, 2019 update]]; please verify changes to [[Hero behavior|AI behavior]]. * [[Hero]]es will often [[spam]] this spell, which will deplete their energy. {{anomaly|Contrary to the full description, this skill causes healing and not [[health gain]].}}
== Trivia == * The name of this skill may be a reference to the Academy Award-winning 1990 film [[w:Reversal of Fortune|Reversal of Fortune]].
== See also == {{see|Order of damage modifiers}}
