==Acquisition== '''[[Hero skill trainer]]s''' *[[Pikin]] ([[Kamadan, Jewel of Istan]]) *[[Shiloh]] ([[Sunspear Great Hall]]) *[[Libeh]] ([[Command Post]])
==Related skills== *{{skill icon|Healing Hands}} ([[elite]]) *{{skill icon|Healing Seed}}
==Notes== *It is the party members of the ''target'' that gets the healing, not those of the caster. **If used on a [[minion]], all allied minions will receive the health instead of party members. *Only the party members in compass range of the target will be healed. *The enchantment ends if the target leaves the caster's compass range. * Combines well with [[Shield of Absorption]] when the target of both enchantments is under heavy attack (e.g. a character [[tank]]ing). *Works very well when used on an [[emo]] who has a [[Life Bond]] on a tank. *This skill will trigger if the damage received is 0, unlike [[Essence Bond]]. {{Anomaly|If two people cast this spell on one target, both will take effect; however, only one enchantment will show on the [[effects monitor]].}} {{Anomaly|The heal amount is based on your rank of [[Divine Favor]] at the time of each hit rather than at the initial casting, i.e. if your attributes are increased/decreased while the enchantment is in effect, the heal amount will change accordingly.}} {{Bug|This skill actually causes [[health gain]].}}
==Trivia== * When casting this spell, it makes the same sound as using a [[signet]]. * This skill has changed since its introduction; see its [[Seed of Life/Skill history|skill history]] for details.
