{{Skill infobox | id = 926 | name = Sharpen Daggers | campaign = Factions | profession = Assassin | attribute = Critical Strikes | type = Enchantment Spell | energy = 5 | recharge = 20 | activation = 1 | causes1 = Bleeding | description = [[Enchantment Spell]]. For {{gr|5|30}} seconds, your [[dagger attack]]s cause [[Bleeding]] for {{gr|5|15}} seconds. | concise description = Enchantment Spell. ({{gr|5|30}} seconds.) Your dagger attacks inflict the Bleeding condition ({{gr|5|15}} seconds). }}
{{Skill progression |attribute = [[Critical Strikes]] |var1 name = [[Duration]] |var2 name = [[Bleeding]] duration |var1 at0 = 5 |var1 at15 = 30 |var2 at0 = 5 |var2 at15 = 15}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Skill trainer]]s''' * [[Zhao Di]] ([[Shing Jea Monastery]]) * [[Xu Fengxia]] ([[Ran Musu Gardens]]) * [[Michiko]] ([[Kaineng Center]])
== Notes == * Bleeding will [[cover]] conditions inflicted by attack skills. * If using with [[Apply Poison]], Poison will cover bleeding. If using with [[Poison Tip Signet]], the condition apply in order, so bleeding will cover poison if Sharpen Daggers is applied second. * Attacks while wielding daggers will trigger the bleeding, so [[Melee Attack]]s are included. ** Combine with [[Whirlwind Attack]] to apply bleeding on a large scale. {{bug|If a [[Ranged attack|ranged]] weapon is swapped for daggers after the attack was made and before the projectile hit, Sharpen Dagger will count this projectile hit as a dagger attack}}
== Trivia == Before the [[Game updates/20090806|August 6, 2009 update]], this skill affected non-dagger attacks as well.
