__NOTOC__{{Skill infobox | name = Shield of Absorption | id = 1399 | campaign = Nightfall | profession = Monk | attribute = Protection Prayers | type = Enchantment Spell | energy = 5 | activation = 1 | recharge = 10 | causes1 = Damage Reduction | description = [[Enchantment Spell]]. For {{gr|3|7}} seconds, [[damage]] received by [[target]] [[ally]] is [[Damage reduction|reduced]] by 5 each time that ally is hit while under the effects of this enchantment. | concise description = Enchantment Spell. ({{gr|3|7}} seconds.) Reduces incoming damage by 5 each time target ally takes damage. }}
{{Skill progression | attribute = [[Protection Prayers]] | var1 at0 = 3 | var1 name = [[Duration]] | var1 at15 = 7}}
== Acquisition == ===[[Unlock]] only=== ;[[Hero]]es *Unlocking [[Tahlkora]]
== Related skills == {{gw2w}} * {{skill icon|Shielding Hands}} * {{skill icon|Stoneflesh Aura}}
== Notes == * The damage reduction increases with every hit received. Damage from the first hit will be reduced by 5, damage from the second by 10, damage from the third by 15 and so on, until the enchantment ends or is recast. * This skill is particularly useful for a [[tank]] absorbing a lot of damage. For a low [[armor rating]] tank being hit rapidly, coupling this skill with [[Spirit Bond]] is extremely beneficial, as Spirit Bond takes care of sustaining the tank at first, and thereafter Shield of Absorption usually reduces any damage to zero. * Combines well with [[Seed of Life]] when the target of both enchantments is under heavy attack (e.g. a character tanking). * One of the better enchantments to use with any way of extending Monk Enchantments, such as the [[Of Enchanting]] Weapon upgrade and [[Blessed Aura]] due to how this enchantment improves its effectiveness the longer it lasts.
== Trivia == * The functionality of this skill has changed since its introduction; see its [[/Skill history|skill revision history]] for details.
[[Category:Skills without known Nightfall trainers]]

