{{Skill infobox | name = Signet of Recall | id = 1993 | campaign = Eye of the North | profession = Mesmer | attribute = Inspiration Magic | type = Signet | activation = 1 | recharge = 20 | fixed eregen = -4 | causes1 = Energy Degeneration | causes2 = Energy Gain | description = [[Signet]]. For 10 seconds, you have -4 [[Energy regeneration]]. When this effect [[End effect|ends]], you gain {{gr|13|20}} Energy. | concise description = Signet. (10 seconds.) You have -4 Energy regeneration. End effect: you gain {{gr|13|20}} Energy.}}
{{Skill progression |attribute = [[Inspiration Magic]] |var1 name = [[Energy]] gain |var1 at0 = 13 |var1 at15 = 20}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Skill trainer]]s''' * [[Micah Fergson]] ([[Eye of the North (outpost)|Eye of the North]]) * [[Sida]] ([[Gunnar's Hold]]) * [[Ybbob]] ([[Rata Sum]])
== Related skills == * {{Skill icon|Ether Signet}} * {{Skill icon|Mantra of Recall}} ([[elite]])
== Notes == * You lose exactly 13 {{1/3}} energy from the -4 [[pip]]s over 10 seconds. * If the signet is renewed before it ends, the caster will gain energy for each time the skill was activated. * [[Ether Signet]] will provide more total energy gain per second than this skill; however, there are several circumstances when Signet of Recall is useful: **When encountering heavy [[energy denial]], e.g. from a [[Mursaat Tower (skill)|Mursaat Tower]] (the energy degeneration from Signet of Recall will have no effect since your energy has already been depleted). **When you already have Ether Signet on your [[skill bar]] and need even more energy without having to use skills that require energy. **When you are facing many short battles (since Signet of Recall can be used right before the battle, during which time the energy degeneration is not disadvantageous). **When [[energy hiding]], you will not lose any energy from this skill while your current energy is 0.

