{{Pveversion|Signet of Spirits}} {{Skill infobox | name = Signet of Spirits (PvP) | id = 2965 | campaign = Factions | profession = Ritualist | attribute = Channeling Magic | type = Signet | elite = y | activation = 1 | recharge = 20 | target = self | causes1 = Energy Gain | description = [[Elite]] [[Signet]]. You gain {{gr|3|12}} [[Energy]] if you are within [[earshot]] of a [[spirit]]. | concise description = Elite Signet. You gain {{gr|3|12}} Energy. {{gray|No effect unless you are within earshot of a spirit.}} | is-pvp = y }}
{{Skill progression | attribute = [[Channeling Magic]] | var1 name = [[Energy]] gain | var1 at0 = 3 | var1 at15 = 12}}
== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Offering of Spirit}} ([[elite]]) * {{skill icon|Signet of Creation}} * {{skill icon|Spirit Channeling}} (elite) * {{skill icon|Spirit Siphon}}
== Notes == * The main difference of this skill compared to its related elite counterparts is the fact that it is a [[signet]]. [[Offering of Spirit]] is a [[spell]] which has a faster activation time and shorter recharge (especially if using weapons providing [[HCT]] and [[HSR]]), on top of that it also ensures energy gain even when not within earshot of a spirit. [[Spirit Channeling]] can return much more energy but is an [[enchantment]] and requires investment in [[Spawning Power]]. * [[Spirit Siphon]] in particular, but also [[Signet of Creation]] and [[Boon of Creation]] (both in Spawning Power) are good, non-elite alternatives if your build uses several spirits.
== Trivia == * The functionality of this skill has changed since its introduction; see its [[Signet of Spirits/Skill history|PvE]] and [[Signet of Spirits (PvP)/Skill history|PvP]] skill revision history for details.
