__NOTOC__{{Skill infobox | name = Soul Taker | campaign = Core | profession = Necromancer | attribute = Soul Reaping | type = Enchantment Spell | pve-only = y | elite = y | energy = 5 | activation = 1 | recharge = 15 | target = untargeted | causes1 = Armor-ignoring Damage | causes2 = Sacrifice | description = [[Elite]] [[Enchantment Spell]]. For {{gr|3|30}} seconds, your attacks [[sacrifice]] {{gr|15|20}} health and deal {{gr|15|20}} more damage. {{gray|PvE Skill}} | concise description = Elite Enchantment Spell. ({{gr|3|30}} seconds.) Attacks deal +{{gr|15|20}} damage and sacrifice {{gr|15|20}} health. {{gray|PvE Skill}} | id = 3423 }} {{Skill progression | attribute = [[Soul Reaping]] | var1 name = [[Duration]] | var1 at0 = 3 | var1 at15 = 30 | var2 name = + Damage | var2 at0 = 15 | var2 at15 = 20 | var3 name = Sacrifice | var3 at0 = 15 | var3 at15 = 20 }}
==Acquisition== '''[[Signet of Capture]]''' *[[Prophecies]] **[[Abaddon's Cursed]] ([[Perdition Rock]]) (requires a party member to be carrying a [[Proof of Triumph]])
==Notes== *This is a [[core]] skill, but [[Guild Wars Prophecies]] is required to obtain the skill. * Usually combined with [[Dark Aura]] for [[AoE]] [[armor-ignoring]] damage. ** [[Live Vicariously]] can help offset the health loss of Dark Aura. * The health sacrifice occurs for each hit rather than for each attack, so skills such as [[Cyclone Axe]] or [[Whirlwind Attack]] can trigger the health sacrifice multiple times, while skills such as [[Vigorous Spirit]] will trigger once. ** [[Blood Bond]] can help offset the health sacrifice. ** This can lead to a [[spike]] when combined with Dark Aura. * The health sacrifice occurs even if the attack [[miss]]es or is [[block]]ed. * The concise description is correct: the damage is [[armor-ignoring]] bonus damage.
{{anomaly|The health sacrifice does not appear on the damage monitor.}}
==Trivia== * This is the only ability that sacrifices a flat amount of health. *This skill uses the same icon as the ''[[Guild Wars 2]]'' [[gw2:Necromancer|Necromancer]] skill [[gw2:Dark Path|Dark Path]]. *Added to the game with the [[Feedback:Game updates/20200422|22nd April 2020 update]] as part of the 15th [[Anniversary Celebration]]. *Prior to the 30th April 2020 patch, life sacrifice also triggered if the attack missed or failed, leading to Dark Aura triggering twice on [[Dual attack]]s out of sequence. * The functionality of this skill has changed since its introduction; see its [[/Skill history|skill revision history]] for details.
