{{Skill infobox | id = 48 | name = Spirit of Failure | campaign = Prophecies | profession = Mesmer | attribute = Inspiration Magic | type = Hex Spell | energy = 15 | activation = 3 | recharge = 20 | causes1 = Miss | causes2 = Energy Gain | description = [[Hex Spell]]. For 30 seconds, [[target]] [[foe]] has a 25% chance to [[miss]] with [[attack]]s. You gain {{gr|1|3}} [[Energy]] whenever that foe fails to hit in combat. | concise description = Hex Spell. (30 seconds.) Target foe has 25% chance to miss. You gain {{gr|1|3}} Energy whenever this foe misses. | target = foes }}
{{Skill progression |attribute = [[Inspiration Magic]] |var1 name = [[Energy]] gain |var1 at0 = 1 |var1 at15 = 3}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Skill quest]]s''' * [[Dropping Eaves]] ([[Ettin's Back]]) '''[[Skill trainer]]s''' * [[Tengsao]] ([[The Amnoon Oasis]]) * [[Dakk]] ([[Ember Light Camp]]) '''[[Signet of Capture]]''' * [[Onan the Spiritless]] ([[Gates of Kryta]]) * [[Bija Gravewailer]] ([[Divinity Coast]])
== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Price of Failure}} * {{skill icon|Reckless Haste}}
== Notes == * This skill triggers when the target [[Fail#Skills that have an effect when an attack fails to hit|fails to hit]]. [[Block]]ing with a skill, [[Line of sight|dodging a ranged attack, or even using the terrain to avoid being hit]] by a [[ranged attack]] will trigger the energy gain. * Great synergy with other effects that further increase the chance to miss, notably the [[Blind]] condition, and to a lesser extent the hexes [[Blurred Vision]], [[Calculated Risk]], [[Price of Failure]] and [[Reckless Haste]]. * Combine with [[Distortion]] for good blocking and energy management. * As with blocking, "missed" hexes combine multiplicatively and not additively. Thus, a foe hexed with both [[Reckless Haste]] and Spirit of Failure has a 62.5% chance to miss with attacks.
