== Acquisition == '''[[Signet of Capture]]''' * [[Joknang Earthturner]] ([[Bahdok Caverns]])
== Related skills == {{see|Doublecast skill}} * {{skill icon|Armor of Earth}} * {{skill icon|Armor of Mist}} * {{skill icon|Armor of Sanctity}} * {{skill icon|Dulled Weapon}} * {{skill icon|Kinetic Armor}} * {{skill icon|Stoneflesh Aura}}
== Notes == * Effective against [[Assassin]]s who use [[Critical Strikes]] to manage their energy. * As with any [[doublecast skill]], [[NPC]]s will use this skill as soon as there is an enemy within the spell's [[area of effect]] range of an ally. * Foes suffer two damage [[packet]]s if the caster is targeted. * If a foe is targeted when Stone Sheath is cast, then the enchantment will automatically target the ally nearest to the foe.
== Trivia == * This skill has changed since its introduction; see its [[Stone Sheath/Skill history|skill history]] for details.
[[de:Steinmantel]]

{{Skill infobox | name = Stone Striker | id = 1371 | campaign = Nightfall | profession = Elementalist | attribute = Earth Magic | type = Enchantment Spell | energy = 5 | activation = {{1/4}} | recharge = 20 | causes1 = Earth Damage | description = [[Enchantment Spell]]. For {{gr|5|30|}} seconds, whenever you take or deal [[elemental damage|elemental]] or [[physical damage]], that [[damage]] is converted to [[earth damage]]. | concise description = Enchantment Spell. ({{gr|5|30}} seconds.) Converts elemental and physical damage you take or deal to earth damage. }}
{{Skill progression |attribute = [[Earth Magic]] |var1 name = [[Duration]] |var1 at0 = 5 |var1 at15 = 30}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Skill trainer]]s''' * [[Zendeht]] ([[Gate of Torment]]) '''[[Hero skill trainer]]s''' * [[Hoju]] (Gate of Torment)
== Notes == {{anomaly|This also converts [[chaos damage|chaos]], [[dark damage|dark]], [[holy damage|damage]] and [[Spirit|spirit attacks]] [[damage type]]s into earth damage.}} {{bug|This skill does not convert damage but instead forces the damage type of all dealt damage to be earth damage. For example when applying winter on top of stone striker, [[physical damage]] is not converted into [[earth damage]], since [[winter]] has no effect on it - it still considers the damage to be of physical type. This is irrespective of which damage converting skill is used first.}} * Good synergy with [[Mantra of Earth]] or [[Storm Chaser]]. * Consider using with [[Geomancer Insignia]], [[Earthbound Insignia]] and a [[shield]] or [[focus item]] with a [["Like a Rolling Stone"]] inscription.
[[Category:Skills offered by hero skill trainers]]

{{Skill infobox | name = Stoneflesh Aura | id = 1375 | campaign = Nightfall | profession = Elementalist | attribute = Earth Magic | type = Enchantment Spell | energy = 10 | activation = 2 | recharge = 15 | causes1 = Damage Reduction | description = [[Enchantment Spell]]. For {{gr|5|15}} seconds, [[damage]] you receive is [[Damage reduction|reduced]] by {{gr|1|31}}, and you are immune to [[critical hit|critical attacks]]. | concise description = Enchantment Spell. ({{gr|5|15}} seconds.) Reduces damage you take by {{gr|1|31}}, and you are immune to critical hits. }}
{{Skill progression | attribute = [[Earth Magic]] | var1 name = [[Duration]] | var1 at0 = 5 | var1 at15 = 15 | var2 name = [[Damage reduction]] | var2 at0 = 1 | var2 at15 = 31}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Skill trainer]]s''' * [[Nightfall]] ** [[Baram]] ([[Kodash Bazaar]]) ** [[Resh]] ([[Yahnur Market]]) '''[[Hero skill trainer]]s''' * Nightfall ** [[Warden of Whispers (Chantry of Secrets)|Warden of Whispers]] ([[Chantry of Secrets]]) '''[[Signet of Capture]]''' * Nightfall ** [[Joknang Earthturner]] ([[Bahdok Caverns]]) ** [[Ajamduk, Hunter of the Sands]] ([[Mehtani Keys]]) * [[Eye of the North]] ** [[Joffs the Mitigator]] ([[Riven Earth]])
== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Armor of Sanctity}} * {{skill icon|Dulled Weapon}} * {{skill icon|Stone Sheath}} ([[elite]])
== Notes == * This skill reduces all types of damage, including [[armor-ignoring damage]]. * This is a popular damage reduction skill for [[farming]], sometimes coupled with [[Protective Spirit]] (cast before Stoneflesh Aura) with less than 330 health, to ensure losing no health at all. This build is known as the 330Hp, similarly to the [[600]] and [[55 Monk]] build. * When removed with a damaging [[List of enchantment removal skills|removal skill]], such as [[Shatter Enchantment]], the damage from the removal will still be reduced. * This skill can be particularly effective against [[Assassin]]s, as many of their builds deal much of their damage through critical hits and rely on them for energy management. {{Bug|This enchantment does not actually make you immune to critical hits, but prevents extra damage from them. As such, effects that may result from them, such as [[knock down]], or the re-applying effect of [[Critical Agility]] and [[Critical Defenses]] will still apply. However, the damage-nullified critical hit will not trigger the energy gain of [[Critical Strikes]].}}
[[Category:Skills offered by hero skill trainers]]

