{{Pveversion|Unyielding Aura}} {{Skill infobox | name = Unyielding Aura (PvP) | id = 2891 | campaign = Prophecies | profession = Monk | attribute = Divine Favor | type = Enchantment Spell | elite = y | upkeep = -1 | energy = 5 | activation = 3 | recharge = 15 | description = [[Elite]] [[Enchantment Spell]]. Bring [[target]] [[Death|dead]] [[party]] member [[Resurrection|back to life]] at full [[Health]] and full [[Energy]]. If you stop [[Upkeep|maintaining]] this enchantment or if this enchantment is removed, that party member dies and leaves an exploited [[corpse]]. Deaths while enchanted with Unyielding Aura do not incur a [[death penalty]]. (50% [[fail]]ure chance with [[Divine Favor]] 4 or less.) | concise description = Elite Enchantment Spell. Resurrects target party member (full Health, full Energy). End effect: this ally dies and leaves an exploited corpse. Does not incur a death penalty. {{gray|50% failure chance unless Divine Favor 5 or more.}} | is-pvp = y | target = dead party members }}
==Related skills== * {{skill icon|Vengeance}}
==Notes== *Make sure the target has a [[cover]] enchantment, since a well-placed [[List of enchantment removal skills|enchantment removal]] from a [[foe]] will cause your party member to die. *Dying while enchanted by this skill does not count as a [[death]]; teams on [[Kill Count]] and [[Alliance Battle]] maps will not be awarded points for deaths of players under the effects of Unyielding Aura.
