{{Skill infobox | id = 268 | name = Unyielding Aura | campaign = Prophecies | profession = Monk | attribute = Divine Favor | type = Enchantment Spell | special = Resurrection | elite = y | upkeep = -1 | energy = 5 | activation = {{1/4}} | recharge = 10 | causes1 = Shadow Step | causes2 = Increased Healing | causes3 = End | description = [[Elite]] [[Enchantment Spell]]. While you [[Upkeep|maintain]] this enchantment, your Monk [[spell]]s [[heal]] for +{{gr|15|60}}% more [[Health]]. When this enchantment [[End effect|ends]] one random other [[party]] member is [[Resurrection|resurrected]] with full Health and [[Energy]] and [[Shadow Step|teleport]]ed to your location. | concise description = Elite Enchantment Spell. Your Monk spells heal for +{{gr|15|60}}%. End effect: a random other party member is resurrected with full Health and Energy and teleported to your location. | aoe = earshot | has-pvp = y | target = self }}
{{Skill progression |attribute = [[Divine Favor]] |var1 name = % Extra [[heal]]ing |var1 at0 = 15 |var1 at15 = 60}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Signet of Capture]]''' * [[Ipillo Wupwup]] ([[Witman's Folly]]) * [[Kaia Wupwup]] ([[Spearhead Peak]], [[Talus Chute]])
== Related skills == {{main|Resurrection|Shadow step}} * {{skill icon|Aura of Faith}} ([[elite]]) * {{skill icon|Healer's Boon}} (elite) * {{skill icon|Life Attunement}} * {{skill icon|Rebirth}} * {{skill icon|Sunspear Rebirth Signet}}
== Notes == * The resurrected party member must be in [[earshot]]. * The resurrected party member cannot activate skills with a cast time for 1 second, although they can still move and use skills with no cast time. * The bonus does not affect [[Health Regeneration]] (such as from [[Healing Breeze]]), the healing from [[Divine Favor]], nor indirect healing from enchantments (such as [[Dwayna's Sorrow]]). For details, see [[Heal#Healing modifiers|healing modifiers]]. * When dismissed, this skill can resurrect even if the caster or target is in [[Frozen Soil]] range. However, it cannot be ''cast'' while under the effects of Frozen Soil. The monk can retreat out of range, cast this skill, move back in and cancel it to resurrect. * If maintaining this skill when you die, another dead party member will resurrect at your corpse. However, if the resurrected party member is a [[hero]] or [[henchman]] with no resurrection skills, your [[death]] counts toward the party [[wipe]]. ** If a party [[resign]]s while one or more of them are maintaining this skill, the enchantments will end and resurrect players even after they have resigned. * Heroes dismiss Unyielding Aura the instant a party member dies in range to resurrect them. They also give a low priority to re-casting it during combat. * This skill, [[Eternal Aura]], [["By Ural's Hammer!"]], and [["We Shall Return!"]] are the fastest resurrection skills. * In parties with death penalty removal consumables in high end quests, resurrecting at full health and especially at full energy is valued greatly over the increase in healing output.
{{Anomaly|The tiny delay between the target being teleported to the casters location and being resurrected is long enough for an AI to possibly use "We Shall Return!", which takes place before UA's resurrecting effect.}} {{bug|If you are moving when it ends, the resurrected party member will be [[teleport]]ed to where you started running or where you last changed direction, not to your current position.}}
== Trivia == * Since the [[Game updates/20080910|September 10, 2008 update]], the dead party member must be within [[casting range]] to be resurrected when the enchantment ends. Before that, this spell would resurrect a party member from any location on the map.
