{{Skill infobox | id = 254 | name = Vigorous Spirit | campaign = Prophecies | profession = Monk | attribute = Healing Prayers | type = Enchantment Spell | energy = 5 | activation = {{1/4}} | recharge = 4 | causes1 = Healing | description = [[Enchantment Spell]]. For 30 seconds, each time [[target]] [[ally]] [[attack]]s or casts a [[spell]], that ally is [[heal]]ed for {{gr|5|20}} [[Health]]. | concise description = Enchantment Spell. (30 seconds.) Heals for {{gr|5|20}} each time target ally attacks or casts a spell. | target = allies }} {{Skill progression | attribute = [[Healing Prayers]] | var1 name = [[Heal]]ing | var1 at0 = 5 | var1 at15 = 20 }}
==Acquisition== '''[[Skill quest]]''' *[[The Wayward Monk]] ([[Yak's Bend]]) '''[[Skill trainer]]s''' *[[Firstwatch Sergio]] ([[Lion's Arch]]) *[[Dakk]] ([[Ember Light Camp]])
==Related skills== *{{skill icon|Live Vicariously}} *{{skill icon|Mystic Vigor}} *{{skill icon|Way of Perfection}}
==Notes== *Because the healing triggers on attacks and not on hits, skills that cause multiple attacks will trigger Vigorous Spirit multiple times, whereas skills that cause only multiple hits trigger Vigorous Spirit once. **The attacker is healed very quickly when attacking with [[daggers]] due to their fast attack speed and chance to [[double strike]]. **Activates with skills like [[Illusionary Weaponry]], since Vigorous Spirit only requires an attack, not a hit. * [[Dervish]]es are a good target for this skill, since they tend to frequently use flash enchantment while simultaneously attacking with melee attacks, both of which triggers the healing.
== Trivia == * The functionality of this skill has changed since its introduction; see its [[/Skill history|skill revision history]] for details.
