__NOTOC__{{Skill infobox | id = 239 | name = Ward Against Harm | campaign = Prophecies | profession = Elementalist | attribute = Water Magic | type = Ward Spell | energy = 15 | activation = 1 | recharge = 20 | elite = y | causes1 = Health Regeneration | causes2 = Increased Armor Rating | description = [[Elite]] [[Ward Spell]]. Create a Ward Against Harm at this location. For {{gr|5|15}} seconds, non-[[spirit]] [[Ally|allies]] [[in the area|in this area]] have +{{gr|1|3}} [[health regeneration]], +{{gr|12|24}} [[Armor rating|armor]], and an additional +{{gr|12|24}} armor against [[elemental damage]]. This spell is [[disable]]d for 20 seconds. | concise description = Elite Ward Spell. ({{gr|5|15}} seconds.) Allies in this ward have +{{gr|1|3}} Health regeneration, +{{gr|12|24}} armor, and +{{gr|12|24}} additional armor against elemental damage. {{gray|Spirits are unaffected. This spell is disabled for 20 seconds.}} | has-pvp = y }}
{{Skill progression | attribute = [[Water Magic]] | var1 name = [[Duration]] | var1 at0 = 5 | var1 at15 = 15 | var2 name = [[Health regeneration]] | var2 at0 = 1 | var2 at15 = 3 | var3 name = +[[Armor rating|Armor]] | var3 at0 = 12 | var3 at15 = 24 | var4 name = +Armor vs [[elemental damage]] | var4 at0 = 12 | var4 at15 = 24}}
== Acquisition == '''[[Signet of Capture]]''' * [[Prophecies]] ** [[Arkhel Havenwood]] ([[Frozen Forest]]) ** [[Perfected Aegis]] ([[The Battle for Lion's Arch (explorable area)]], only during [[The Battle for Lion's Arch]]) * [[Eye of the North]] **[[Frazar Frostfur]] ([[Against the Charr]]) ** [[Spafrod Iceblood]] ([[Sacnoth Valley]], only after [[Assault on the Stronghold]])
== Related skills == * {{skill icon|Ebon Battle Standard of Courage}} * {{skill icon|Ward Against Elements}}
== Notes == {{bug|This skill does not actually become disabled, as it can be instantly recharged by [[Glyph of Renewal]], and the recharge reduced by [[Glyph of Swiftness]].}} * The ward actually grants +{{gr|12|24}} armor against non-elemental damage and +{{gr|24|48}} against elemental damage. This distinction is important for the [[Effect stacking|armor cap]] and [[armor calculation]]. * The AI cannot detect a ward's presence. While remaining inside would be favourable, even flagged NPCs characters will run out of its protection whenever hit.
== Trivia ==
* Prior to the release of [[Time Ward]], this was the only elite ward spell. This and [[Teinai's Heat]] are the only Elementalist ward spells outside of [[Earth Magic]]. * This is one of five elite skills seen in [[pre-Searing Ascalon]], the other four being [[Barrage]], [[Bull's Charge]], [[Earth Shaker]], and [[Hundred Blades]]. * [[Elementalist Aziure]] enlists the player to [[The Elementalist Experiment|help her research this skill]].
