== Acquisition == '''[[Skill trainer]]s''' * [[Eye of the North]] ** [[Micah Fergson]] ([[Eye of the North (outpost)|Eye of the North]]) ** [[Sida]] ([[Gunnar's Hold]]) ** [[Ybbob]] ([[Rata Sum]])
== Notes == {{bug| Similar to [[Ward of Stability]], this ward spell's [[recharge time]] cannot be decreased. E.g. activating this ward spell while under the effects of [[Glyph of Renewal]] or [[Glyph of Swiftness]] will consume the glyph, but the recharge time will not be decreased. However, the recharge time can be increased, e.g. by [[Glyph of Sacrifice]].}} {{anomaly|The weakness duration is independent of duration modifiers such as the [[Heavy]] weapon upgrade.}} * This skill applies weakness after a skill's weakness check. For instance, if you were to hit a foe with [[Stoning]] while in the ward, the knock down due to Stoning's weakness trigger will not happen, as the weakness is applied after the spell completes. == Trivia == * This skill was renamed from '''Ward of Weariness'''.

